/-! ### В§10.157 Fourier synthesis from в„“ВІ-summable coefficients

Mathlib's `mFourierBasis` is a `HilbertBasis (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) в„Ӯ` on
`LВІ(рқ•ӢВІ)`; its representation map `mFourierBasis.repr` is a linear
isometry equivalence into `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2`.  Its inverse
gives the Fourier-synthesis map: from an в„“ВІ-summable coefficient
sequence, construct the corresponding `Lp` element.

В§10.157 supplies the concrete `Оё_lim t` operator that discharges the
`Оё_lim` input of `HasFourierSynthesis.ofPerModeLimit` (В§10.154.B), as
long as the per-mode limit `per.b В· t` is в„“ВІ-summable at every `t вүҘ 0`
(which follows from the uniform `LВІ` bound on the Galerkin sequence +
Fatou on `в„“ВІ(в„ӨВІ)`). -/

/-- **В§10.157.A  Fourier synthesis `Lp` element from an в„“ВІ sequence.**
Lifts `b вҲҲ в„“ВІ(в„ӨВІ)` to the corresponding `LВІ(рқ•ӢВІ)` element via
`mFourierBasis.repr.symm`. -/
noncomputable def fourierSynthesisLp
    (b : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2) :
    Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  mFourierBasis.repr.symm b

/-- **В§10.157.B  Fourier coefficients of the Fourier synthesis recover
the input sequence.**  `mFourierCoeff (fourierSynthesisLp b) m = b m`
for every mode `m`. -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_fourierSynthesisLp
    (b : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) :
    mFourierCoeff (fourierSynthesisLp b) m = b m := by
  have h_repr : mFourierBasis.repr (fourierSynthesisLp b) = b := by
    unfold fourierSynthesisLp
    exact LinearIsometryEquiv.apply_symm_apply _ _
  have := congrArg (fun (v : lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2) => v m) h_repr
  simp only [mFourierBasis_repr] at this
  exact this

/-! ### В§10.158 `Оё_lim` construction via `fourierSynthesisLp`

Composes В§10.157's `fourierSynthesisLp` with an `lp`-valued per-mode
limit `bLp : в„қ вҶ’ lp (fun _ => в„Ӯ) 2` into the concrete
`Оё_lim : в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2` operator required by `HasFourierSynthesis.ofPerModeLimit`
(В§10.154.B).  The Fourier coefficients of the constructed `Оё_lim`
match `per.b В· t` at every `t вүҘ 0` by composing В§10.157.B with the
`bLp вҶ” per.b` agreement hypothesis.

В§10.158 reduces the remaining `Оё_lim` content of `HasFourierSynthesis`
(Target #2) to a single concrete ingredient: an `lp`-valued per-mode
limit `bLp` matching `per.b`.  Producing `bLp` from `per` + an в„“ВІ-summability
hypothesis at every `t вүҘ 0` is a straightforward wrap using mathlib's
`Memв„“p`-from-summable bridge (deferred to a follow-up session). -/

/-- **В§10.158.A  Concrete `Оё_lim` operator via Fourier synthesis.**
Given an `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2`-valued function `bLp` of time,
produces the corresponding `Lp в„Ӯ 2`-valued trajectory via pointwise
Fourier synthesis. -/
noncomputable def ОёLimOfLp
    (bLp : в„қ вҶ’ lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2) :
    в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  fun t => fourierSynthesisLp (bLp t)

/-- **В§10.158.C  `lp` element from summable-square-norm sequence.**
Builds the `lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2` element whose underlying
function is `b`, given that `Summable (fun m => вҖ–b mвҖ– ^ 2)`.  Uses
mathlib's `memв„“p_gen_iff` (which states `Memв„“p f p вҶ” Summable (fun i =>
вҖ–f iвҖ– ^ p.toReal)` for `0 < p.toReal`).  Supplies the elementary link
from per-mode в„“ВІ summability to the `lp`-valued input of `ОёLimOfLp`. -/
noncomputable def lpOfSummableSqNorm
    (b : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (hSum : Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–b mвҖ– ^ 2) :
    lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2 := by
  refine вҹЁb, ?_вҹ©
  have hp : (0 : в„қ) < (2 : ENNReal).toReal := by
    rw [ENNReal.toReal_ofNat]; norm_num
  refine (memв„“p_gen_iff hp).mpr ?_
  simpa [ENNReal.toReal_ofNat] using hSum

/-- **В§10.158.D  `lpOfSummableSqNorm` coefficient recovery.** -/
theorem lpOfSummableSqNorm_coeff
    (b : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (hSum : Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–b mвҖ– ^ 2)
    (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) :
    (lpOfSummableSqNorm b hSum) m = b m :=
  rfl

/-- **В§10.158.B  Fourier coefficients of `ОёLimOfLp` match the per-mode
limit.**  For every `t вүҘ 0` at which the `bLp` sequence agrees with
`per.b`, the constructed `ОёLimOfLp` has Fourier coefficients exactly
`per.b В· t`. -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_ОёLimOfLp
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    (bLp : в„қ вҶ’ lp (fun _ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => в„Ӯ) 2)
    (h_agree : вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ (bLp t) m = per.b m t)
    (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ) (ht : 0 вүӨ t) :
    mFourierCoeff (ОёLimOfLp bLp t) m = per.b m t := by
  unfold ОёLimOfLp
  rw [mFourierCoeff_fourierSynthesisLp, h_agree m t ht]

/-! ### В§10.159 `HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable` вҖ” the cleanest
constructor for Target #2

Composes В§10.154.B (coefficient-injectivity bridge) with В§10.157
(Fourier synthesis) + В§10.158 (lp-valued Оё_lim) into a single
top-level constructor that takes:

* `per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ` вҖ” output of ArzelГ вҖ“Ascoli + Cantor diagonal
  (still a named classical hypothesis via В§10.155.B)
* `Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2` + initial coefficient match `per.b m 0 = mFourierCoeff Оё m`
* `hSum` вҖ” в„“ВІ-summability of `per.b В· t` at every `t вүҘ 0` (from the
  uniform LВІ Galerkin bound + Fatou on `в„“ВІ`)
* `h_L2` вҖ” strong-LВІ convergence of the extracted Galerkin sequence
  to the constructed `Оё_lim` (Parseval + DCT on `в„“ВІ`)

and produces `HasFourierSynthesis per Оё`.  The `Оё_lim` field is
constructed internally via `ОёLimOfSummable` вҖ” the caller no longer
supplies any `Lp`-valued witness directly; only the elementary
summability + initial match + classical strong-LВІ convergence.
-/

/-- **В§10.159.A  Concrete `Оё_lim` from per-mode limit + summability.**
Builds the `Оё_lim : в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2` operator used by `HasFourierSynthesis`
directly from `per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ` and an в„“ВІ-summability
hypothesis on `per.b В· t` at every `t вүҘ 0`.

On `0 вүӨ t`: the Fourier synthesis of the `lp` element built by
В§10.158.C (`lpOfSummableSqNorm`).
On `t < 0`: `0` (any value; `HasFourierSynthesis` only requires
behaviour for `t вүҘ 0`). -/
noncomputable def ОёLimOfSummable
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2) :
    в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))) :=
  fun t =>
    if ht : 0 вүӨ t then
      fourierSynthesisLp (lpOfSummableSqNorm (fun m => per.b m t) (hSum t ht))
    else 0

/-- **В§10.159.B  Fourier coefficients of `ОёLimOfSummable` match `per.b`.** -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_ОёLimOfSummable
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ) (ht : 0 вүӨ t) :
    mFourierCoeff (ОёLimOfSummable per hSum t) m = per.b m t := by
  unfold ОёLimOfSummable
  rw [dif_pos ht]
  rw [mFourierCoeff_fourierSynthesisLp, lpOfSummableSqNorm_coeff]

/-- **В§10.159.C  `HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable` вҖ” top-level Target #2
constructor.**  Assembles `HasFourierSynthesis per Оё` from the
elementary inputs: per-mode summability + initial coefficient match +
strong-LВІ convergence to the constructed `Оё_lim`.  The `Оё_lim`
itself is built internally вҖ” the caller supplies no `Lp`-valued
witness directly. -/
noncomputable def HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hInit_b : вҲҖ m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө, per.b m 0 = mFourierCoeff Оё m)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (h_L2 : вҲҖ (t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : в„• =>
          вҲ« x, вҖ–galerkinToLp (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) x
                - ОёLimOfSummable per hSum t xвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0)) :
    HasFourierSynthesis per Оё :=
  HasFourierSynthesis.ofPerModeLimit per hInit_b
    (ОёLimOfSummable per hSum)
    (fun m t ht => mFourierCoeff_ОёLimOfSummable per hSum m t ht)
    h_L2

/-! ### В§10.160 Parseval on a difference вҖ” building block for strong-LВІ

The strong-`LВІ` convergence proof in `HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable`
(В§10.159.C) needs to express `вҲ« вҖ–f - gвҖ–ВІ` as a per-mode sum of
squared Fourier-coefficient differences.  This is Parseval applied to
`f - g`, combined with the linearity
`mFourierCoeff (f - g) m = mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m`.

В§10.160 factors this as a standalone lemma so later discharges of
`h_L2` can consume it directly, without re-deriving the Parseval
step each time. -/

/-- **В§10.160  Parseval on a difference.**  For any two `LВІ(рқ•ӢВІ)`
elements `f, g`:
`вҲ« вҖ–f x - g xвҖ–ВІ dx = вҲ‘' m, вҖ–mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g mвҖ–ВІ`. -/
theorem integral_norm_sq_sub_eq_tsum_sq_mFourierCoeff_sub
    (f g : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))) :
    (вҲ« x, вҖ–f x - g xвҖ– ^ 2) =
    вҲ‘' m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө, вҖ–mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2 := by
  -- Parseval on `(f - g)` at the `Lp` level.
  have h_pars : HasSum (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–mFourierCoeff (f - g) mвҖ– ^ 2)
      (вҲ« x, вҖ–(f - g) xвҖ– ^ 2) := hasSum_sq_mFourierCoeff (f - g)
  -- Linearity of `mFourierCoeff` on the difference via `mFourierCoeffLM`.
  have h_sub : вҲҖ m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө,
      mFourierCoeff (f - g) m = mFourierCoeff f m - mFourierCoeff g m := by
    intro m
    show mFourierCoeffLM m (f - g) = mFourierCoeffLM m f - mFourierCoeffLM m g
    rw [map_sub]
  -- `вҖ–(f - g) xвҖ–ВІ = вҖ–f x - g xвҖ–ВІ` a.e. (via `Lp` subtraction coercion).
  have h_ae : (fun x => вҖ–(f - g) xвҖ– ^ 2) =бөҗ[volume]
      fun x => вҖ–f x - g xвҖ– ^ 2 := by
    filter_upwards [Lp.coeFn_sub f g] with x hx
    rw [hx, Pi.sub_apply]
  -- Integrals agree by a.e. equality.
  have h_int_eq : (вҲ« x, вҖ–(f - g) xвҖ– ^ 2) = вҲ« x, вҖ–f x - g xвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    integral_congr_ae h_ae
  rw [вҶҗ h_int_eq, вҶҗ h_pars.tsum_eq]
  exact tsum_congr (fun m => by rw [h_sub m])

/-! ### В§10.161 Galerkin-to-`ОёLim` squared difference as per-mode в„“ВІ sum

Combines В§10.160 (Parseval on a difference) with
`mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp` (existing) and
`mFourierCoeff_ОёLimOfSummable` (В§10.159.B) to express the squared
`LВІ`-norm of the difference between the extracted Galerkin truncation
and the `Оё_lim` operator constructed from a summable per-mode limit as
a per-mode в„“ВІ sum of coefficient differences.

This is the bridge from the `LВІ` side (where strong convergence lives)
to the `в„“ВІ(в„ӨВІ)` side (where per-mode convergence + DCT applies).  Once
strong-`LВІ` convergence reduces to `Tendsto (вҲ‘' m, вҖ–В·вҖ–ВІ) atTop (рқ“қ 0)`,
the remaining argument is classical в„“ВІ analysis. -/

/-- **В§10.161  Galerkin-to-`ОёLim` squared `LВІ`-difference as per-mode
в„“ВІ sum.**  For the extracted Galerkin subsequence at every `t вүҘ 0`:
`вҲ« вҖ–galerkinToLp (sqgBox (nsub k)) (Оұ (nsub k) t) x - ОёLimOfSummable per hSum t xвҖ–ВІ dx
  = вҲ‘' m, вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (Оұ (nsub k) t) m - per.b m tвҖ–ВІ`. -/
theorem integral_norm_sq_galerkin_sub_ОёLim_eq_tsum
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (k : в„•) (t : в„қ) (ht : 0 вүӨ t) :
    (вҲ« x, вҖ–galerkinToLp (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) x
            - ОёLimOfSummable per hSum t xвҖ– ^ 2)
    = вҲ‘' m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө,
        вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) m
          - per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2 := by
  rw [integral_norm_sq_sub_eq_tsum_sq_mFourierCoeff_sub]
  refine tsum_congr (fun m => ?_)
  rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp,
      mFourierCoeff_ОёLimOfSummable per hSum m t ht]

/-! ### В§10.162 Strong-LВІ convergence reduces to per-mode в„“ВІ convergence

В§10.161 expressed the squared `LВІ`-distance from the extracted Galerkin
truncation to `ОёLimOfSummable` as a per-mode `в„“ВІ` sum of coefficient
differences.  В§10.162 packages the `Tendsto` version: if that per-mode
`в„“ВІ` sum tends to zero along the extraction subsequence, so does the
`LВІ`-integral.

This is a one-line wrapper via `Tendsto.congr` on В§10.161.  It discharges
the `h_L2` hypothesis of `HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable` (В§10.159.C) at
the `Lp`-integral level, reducing it to a pure `в„“ВІ`-convergence
statement.  The remaining classical analysis вҖ” showing the `в„“ВІ`-sum of
coefficient differences tends to zero from per-mode convergence plus
tightness вҖ” lives entirely on `в„“ВІ(в„ӨВІ)` with no `Lp`-coercion bookkeeping. -/

/-- **В§10.162  Strong-`LВІ` convergence вҮҗ per-mode `в„“ВІ`-convergence.**  If
the per-mode `в„“ВІ` sum `вҲ‘' m, вҖ–galerkinExtend_(nsub k) t m - per.b m tвҖ–ВІ`
tends to zero, so does the corresponding `LВІ`-integral.  Discharges
`h_L2` of В§10.159.C at the `Lp`-integral level, leaving a pure
`в„“ВІ`-convergence statement as the remaining classical input. -/
theorem tendsto_integral_norm_sq_galerkin_sub_ОёLim_of_tsum
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (h_tsum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : в„• =>
          вҲ‘' m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө,
            вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) m
              - per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (t : в„қ) (ht : 0 вүӨ t) :
    Filter.Tendsto
      (fun k : в„• =>
        вҲ« x, вҖ–galerkinToLp (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) x
                - ОёLimOfSummable per hSum t xвҖ– ^ 2)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  refine (h_tsum t ht).congr (fun k => ?_)
  exact (integral_norm_sq_galerkin_sub_ОёLim_eq_tsum per hSum k t ht).symm

/-! ### В§10.163 Pure в„“ВІ Vitali convergence вҖ” tight-family convergence

В§10.162 reduced the `h_L2` input of В§10.159.C to a per-mode в„“ВІ Tendsto
statement.  В§10.163 is the general-в„“ВІ Vitali lemma that closes that
Tendsto from two elementary ingredients:

* **Per-mode convergence**: `f k i вҶ’ g i` pointwise in `k` at each `i`.
* **Uniform в„“ВІ-tail tightness on the differences**: for every `Оө > 0`
  there is a finite `F : Finset О№` such that the tail of the
  squared-difference в„“ВІ sum is `вүӨ Оө` **uniformly in `k`**.

Together these imply `вҲ‘' i, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ–ВІ вҶ’ 0` as `k вҶ’ вҲһ`.  The proof
splits the full tsum at `F` using `Summable.sum_add_tsum_subtype_compl`,
bounds the finite part via `tendsto_finset_sum` on pointwise convergence,
and bounds the tail by the tightness hypothesis.

The statement is free of SQG-specifics so the lemma lives in the pure
в„“ВІ layer.  В§10.164 below specialises it back to the Galerkin setting. -/

/-- **В§10.163  Vitali в„“ВІ convergence on squared differences.**  Per-mode
pointwise convergence `f k В· вҶ’ g` plus uniform в„“ВІ-tail tightness on the
squared differences (Оө-Finset `F` bounding the tail вүӨ Оө for every `k`)
plus summability of each squared-difference family gives
`вҲ‘' i, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ–ВІ вҶ’ 0` as `k вҶ’ вҲһ`. -/
theorem tsum_sq_sub_tendsto_zero_of_tight
    {О№ : Type*} {f : в„• вҶ’ О№ вҶ’ в„Ӯ} {g : О№ вҶ’ в„Ӯ}
    (h_ptw : вҲҖ i, Filter.Tendsto (fun k => f k i) Filter.atTop (nhds (g i)))
    (h_sum_diff : вҲҖ k, Summable fun i => вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2)
    (h_tight : вҲҖ Оө : в„қ, 0 < Оө вҶ’ вҲғ F : Finset О№, вҲҖ k : в„•,
      (вҲ‘' i : { i // i вҲү F }, вҖ–f k i.val - g i.valвҖ– ^ 2) вүӨ Оө) :
    Filter.Tendsto (fun k : в„• => вҲ‘' i, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
  rw [Metric.tendsto_atTop]
  intro Оө hОө
  have hОө2 : (0 : в„қ) < Оө / 2 := by linarith
  obtain вҹЁF, hFвҹ© := h_tight (Оө / 2) hОө2
  -- Per-mode squared differences tend to 0.
  have h_sq_ptw : вҲҖ i : О№,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k => вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
    intro i
    have h1 : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => f k i - g i) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
      simpa using (h_ptw i).sub_const (g i)
    have h2 : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ–) Filter.atTop (nhds (0 : в„қ)) := by
      simpa [norm_zero] using h1.norm
    simpa using h2.pow 2
  -- Finite sum of squared differences tends to 0.
  have h_sum_fin : Filter.Tendsto
      (fun k : в„• => вҲ‘ i вҲҲ F, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2) Filter.atTop (nhds 0) := by
    have := tendsto_finset_sum F (fun i (_ : i вҲҲ F) => h_sq_ptw i)
    simpa using this
  -- Extract `N` beyond which the finite sum is `< Оө/2`.
  obtain вҹЁN, hNвҹ© := Metric.tendsto_atTop.mp h_sum_fin (Оө / 2) hОө2
  refine вҹЁN, fun k hk => ?_вҹ©
  -- Split the full tsum at `F`.
  have hsplit : (вҲ‘' i, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2) =
      (вҲ‘ i вҲҲ F, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2) +
      вҲ‘' i : { i // i вҲү F }, вҖ–f k i.val - g i.valвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    ((h_sum_diff k).sum_add_tsum_subtype_compl F).symm
  -- Non-negativity of the various pieces.
  have h_total_nonneg : (0 : в„қ) вүӨ вҲ‘' i, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    tsum_nonneg (fun _ => sq_nonneg _)
  have h_fin_nonneg : (0 : в„қ) вүӨ вҲ‘ i вҲҲ F, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    Finset.sum_nonneg (fun _ _ => sq_nonneg _)
  -- Bound the finite part by `Оө/2`.
  have h_fin_bound : вҲ‘ i вҲҲ F, вҖ–f k i - g iвҖ– ^ 2 < Оө / 2 := by
    have := hN k hk
    rw [Real.dist_eq, sub_zero, abs_of_nonneg h_fin_nonneg] at this
    exact this
  -- Combine.
  rw [Real.dist_eq, sub_zero, abs_of_nonneg h_total_nonneg, hsplit]
  have h_tail_bound : (вҲ‘' i : { i // i вҲү F }, вҖ–f k i.val - g i.valвҖ– ^ 2) вүӨ Оө / 2 := hF k
  linarith

/-! ### В§10.164 `HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight` вҖ” drop-in capstone

Composes В§10.159.C (`ofSummable`) with В§10.162 (integral вҶ’ tsum reduction)
and В§10.163 (tight-family в„“ВІ Vitali convergence) into a single top-level
constructor that takes only elementary tight-family inputs.

Once the caller supplies per-mode summability (Fatou + uniform в„“ВІ bound)
plus summability/tightness of the coefficient *differences*, the `h_L2`
hypothesis of В§10.159.C is discharged entirely internally.  No `Lp`
coercion bookkeeping reaches the caller, and strong-`LВІ` convergence is
produced from the pure в„“ВІ Vitali argument of В§10.163.

This is the maximally-closed form of `HasFourierSynthesis` construction
reachable without an additional compactness input: every non-structural
hypothesis is now an elementary в„“ВІ-level statement on the coefficient
sequence, with no `Lp`, `Parseval`, or `Fatou`-level analysis required
of the caller. -/

/-- **В§10.164  `HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight` вҖ” Tight-family capstone.**
Builds `HasFourierSynthesis per Оё` from the four elementary в„“ВІ-level
inputs:

* `hInit_b` вҖ” initial coefficient match at `t = 0`.
* `hSum` вҖ” per-mode в„“ВІ-summability of `per.b В· t` at every `t вүҘ 0`.
* `h_sum_diff` вҖ” per-mode в„“ВІ-summability of the Galerkin-to-limit
  coefficient differences at every `t вүҘ 0` and `k : в„•`.
* `h_tight` вҖ” uniform в„“ВІ-tail tightness on those coefficient differences.

`h_L2` of В§10.159.C is discharged internally via В§10.162 + В§10.163. -/
noncomputable def HasFourierSynthesis.ofTight
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (per : HasPerModeLimit Оұ)
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hInit_b : вҲҖ m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө, per.b m 0 = mFourierCoeff Оё m)
    (hSum : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => вҖ–per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (h_sum_diff : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ k : в„•,
      Summable fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) m
          - per.b m tвҖ– ^ 2)
    (h_tight : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ Оө : в„қ, 0 < Оө вҶ’
      вҲғ F : Finset (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), вҲҖ k : в„•,
        (вҲ‘' m : { m // m вҲү F },
          вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox (per.nsub k)) (Оұ (per.nsub k) t) m.val
            - per.b m.val tвҖ– ^ 2) вүӨ Оө) :
    HasFourierSynthesis per Оё :=
  HasFourierSynthesis.ofSummable per hInit_b hSum
    (fun t ht =>
      tendsto_integral_norm_sq_galerkin_sub_ОёLim_of_tsum per hSum
        (fun t' ht' =>
          tsum_sq_sub_tendsto_zero_of_tight
            (fun m => per.tendsto_modeCoeff m t' ht')
            (h_sum_diff t' ht')
            (h_tight t' ht'))
        t ht)

/-! ### В§10.165.A BolzanoвҖ“Weierstrass for bounded в„Ӯ-valued sequences

Wrapper around mathlib's `tendsto_subseq_of_bounded` specialised to the
proper metric space `в„Ӯ`.  Every bounded sequence in `в„Ӯ` admits a
convergent subsequence. -/

/-- **В§10.165.A  BolzanoвҖ“Weierstrass on `в„Ӯ`.**  Any sequence `s : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ`
bounded in norm by some `M` has a strictly-monotone extractor `ПҶ : в„• вҶ’ в„•`
and a limit `L : в„Ӯ` such that `s вҲҳ ПҶ вҶ’ L`. -/
theorem exists_convergent_subseq_of_bounded_complex
    {s : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ} (M : в„қ) (hs : вҲҖ n, вҖ–s nвҖ– вүӨ M) :
    вҲғ ПҶ : в„• вҶ’ в„•, StrictMono ПҶ вҲ§ вҲғ L : в„Ӯ,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k : в„• => s (ПҶ k)) Filter.atTop (nhds L) := by
  have hB : Bornology.IsBounded (Metric.closedBall (0 : в„Ӯ) M) :=
    Metric.isBounded_closedBall
  have hIn : вҲҖ n, s n вҲҲ Metric.closedBall (0 : в„Ӯ) M := by
    intro n
    rw [Metric.mem_closedBall, dist_zero_right]
    exact hs n
  obtain вҹЁL, _hL, ПҶ, hПҶ, htendsвҹ© := tendsto_subseq_of_bounded hB hIn
  exact вҹЁПҶ, hПҶ, L, htendsвҹ©

/-! ### В§10.165.B Cantor diagonal for a countable family of bounded в„Ӯ-sequences

Given a countable family `s : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ` with each row `s i В· `
uniformly bounded, classical Cantor diagonal across `i` produces one
strictly-monotone extractor `nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•` such that `s i вҲҳ nsub`
converges for every `i`.

**Construction.**  Build stages `ОҰ : в„• вҶ’ (в„• вҶ’ в„•)` with `ОҰ 0` the BW
extractor for `s 0` and `ОҰ (i+1) = ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ_{i+1}` where `ПҲ_{i+1}` is the
BW extractor of `s (i+1) вҲҳ ОҰ i`.  The diagonal `nsub k := ОҰ k k` is
strictly monotone (each `ПҲ_j` is strictly monotone, so the stage
compositions preserve strict order on the diagonal), and for every `i`,
the tail `{nsub k : k вүҘ i}` is a reindexing of `ОҰ i` through a
strictly-monotone function, so inherits convergence at row `i`. -/

/-- **В§10.165.B  Cantor diagonal.**  Given a countable family `s i : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ`
of uniformly-bounded complex sequences, produce one subsequence extractor
`nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•` with pointwise convergence along every row `i`. -/
theorem cantor_diagonal_complex
    (s : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ)
    (hs : вҲҖ i : в„•, вҲғ M : в„қ, вҲҖ n : в„•, вҖ–s i nвҖ– вүӨ M) :
    вҲғ nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•, StrictMono nsub вҲ§
      вҲғ L : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ, вҲҖ i : в„•,
        Filter.Tendsto (fun k : в„• => s i (nsub k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
  classical
  -- Helper: pick a BW extractor packaged as a strict-mono function + limit.
  let bwPick : вҲҖ (Пғ : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ) (_ : вҲғ M, вҲҖ n, вҖ–Пғ nвҖ– вүӨ M),
      { p : (в„• вҶ’ в„•) Г— в„Ӯ //
        StrictMono p.1 вҲ§ Filter.Tendsto (fun k => Пғ (p.1 k)) Filter.atTop (nhds p.2) } :=
    fun Пғ hПғ => Classical.indefiniteDescription _ (by
      obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hПғ
      obtain вҹЁПҶ, hПҶ, L, hLвҹ© := exists_convergent_subseq_of_bounded_complex M hM
      exact вҹЁ(ПҶ, L), hПҶ, hLвҹ©)
  -- Define the stages recursively.  `stage i = (ОҰ_i, L_i)` with `ОҰ_i` strictMono,
  -- `Filter.Tendsto (s i вҲҳ ОҰ_i) atTop (рқ“қ L_i)`, and `ОҰ_(i+1) = ОҰ_i вҲҳ ПҲ_(i+1)`
  -- for `ПҲ_(i+1)` the BW extractor of `s (i+1) вҲҳ ОҰ_i`.
  let ОҰ : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„• := fun i => Nat.rec
      ((bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).val.1)
      (fun j prev =>
        prev вҲҳ (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (prev k))
          (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (j + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (prev n)вҹ©)).val.1)
      i
  let L : в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ := fun i => Nat.rec
      ((bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).val.2)
      (fun j prev => (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ОҰ j k))
        (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (j + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ j n)вҹ©)).val.2)
      i
  -- Each ОҰ i is strictly monotone.
  have hОҰ_mono : вҲҖ i, StrictMono (ОҰ i) := by
    intro i
    induction i with
    | zero => exact (bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).property.1
    | succ j ih =>
      refine ih.comp ?_
      exact (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ОҰ j k))
        (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (j + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ j n)вҹ©)).property.1
  -- Stage 0 convergence.
  have hОҰ0_tendsto : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s 0 (ОҰ 0 k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L 0)) :=
    (bwPick (s 0) (hs 0)).property.2
  -- Stage (i+1) convergence.
  have hОҰsucc_tendsto : вҲҖ i,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s (i + 1) (ОҰ (i + 1) k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L (i + 1))) := by
    intro i
    -- By construction, ОҰ (i + 1) k = ОҰ i (ПҲ_(i+1) k) where ПҲ_(i+1) is the BW extractor.
    -- And L (i + 1) = limit of s (i+1) вҲҳ ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ_(i+1).
    exact (bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ОҰ i k))
      (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (i + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ i n)вҹ©)).property.2
  -- Consecutive stages: ОҰ (i+1) = ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ for some strictMono ПҲ.
  have hОҰ_factor : вҲҖ i, вҲғ ПҲ : в„• вҶ’ в„•, StrictMono ПҲ вҲ§ ОҰ (i + 1) = ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ := by
    intro i
    refine вҹЁ(bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ОҰ i k))
      (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (i + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ i n)вҹ©)).val.1,
      (bwPick (fun k => s (i + 1) (ОҰ i k))
        (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (i + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ i n)вҹ©)).property.1, rflвҹ©
  -- Chain: for k вүҘ i, ОҰ k = ОҰ i вҲҳ (some strictMono ПҲ), via induction on (k - i).
  have hОҰ_chain : вҲҖ i k, вҲғ ПҲ : в„• вҶ’ в„•, StrictMono ПҲ вҲ§ ОҰ (i + k) = ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ := by
    intro i k
    induction k with
    | zero => exact вҹЁid, strictMono_id, rflвҹ©
    | succ j ih =>
      obtain вҹЁПҲ, hПҲ_mono, hПҲ_eqвҹ© := ih
      obtain вҹЁПҲ', hПҲ'_mono, hПҲ'_eqвҹ© := hОҰ_factor (i + j)
      refine вҹЁПҲ вҲҳ ПҲ', hПҲ_mono.comp hПҲ'_mono, ?_вҹ©
      show ОҰ (i + (j + 1)) = ОҰ i вҲҳ (ПҲ вҲҳ ПҲ')
      have heq : i + (j + 1) = (i + j) + 1 := by ring
      rw [heq, hПҲ'_eq, вҶҗ Function.comp_assoc, вҶҗ hПҲ_eq]
  -- Diagonal.
  let nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„• := fun k => ОҰ k k
  -- Strict monotonicity.
  have hnsub_mono : StrictMono nsub := by
    intro a b hab
    show ОҰ a a < ОҰ b b
    obtain вҹЁПҲ, hПҲ_mono, hПҲ_eqвҹ© := hОҰ_chain a (b - a)
    have heq : a + (b - a) = b := Nat.add_sub_of_le (le_of_lt hab)
    rw [heq] at hПҲ_eq
    rw [hПҲ_eq]
    show ОҰ a a < ОҰ a (ПҲ b)
    apply hОҰ_mono a
    have hПҲ_ge : b вүӨ ПҲ b := hПҲ_mono.id_le b
    exact lt_of_lt_of_le hab hПҲ_ge
  refine вҹЁnsub, hnsub_mono, L, ?_вҹ©
  intro i
  -- Convergence at row i: tail of nsub (from index вүҘ i) is a strictMono
  -- reindexing of ОҰ i.  Build Ој : в„• вҶ’ в„• so that nsub (i + j) = ОҰ i (Ој j)
  -- with Ој strictMono, then conclude via Tendsto.comp.
  -- Concretely: for each j, hОҰ_chain i j gives ПҲ_j strictMono with
  -- ОҰ (i + j) = ОҰ i вҲҳ ПҲ_j, so nsub (i + j) = ОҰ i (ПҲ_j (i + j)).
  -- Set Ој j := ПҲ_j (i + j) and prove Ој strictMono.
  -- The ПҲ_j's here are chosen via `Classical.choose`; since hОҰ_chain's output
  -- is pulled from a specific term, consistency across j requires care.
  -- Cleaner: use the concrete `ПҲ : в„• вҶ’ (в„• вҶ’ в„•)` built into the recursion.
  --
  -- Define ПҲ i (j) := the "increment extractor" at stage (i + j вҶ’ i + j + 1).
  let ПҲinc : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„• := fun j =>
    (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ОҰ j k))
      (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (j + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ j n)вҹ©)).val.1
  -- By construction, ОҰ (j + 1) = ОҰ j вҲҳ ПҲinc j.
  have hПҲinc_mono : вҲҖ j, StrictMono (ПҲinc j) := fun j =>
    (bwPick (fun k => s (j + 1) (ОҰ j k))
      (by obtain вҹЁM, hMвҹ© := hs (j + 1); exact вҹЁM, fun n => hM (ОҰ j n)вҹ©)).property.1
  have hОҰ_succ_eq : вҲҖ j, ОҰ (j + 1) = ОҰ j вҲҳ ПҲinc j := fun _ => rfl
  -- Оё i j : the composition of ПҲinc i, ПҲinc (i+1), ..., ПҲinc (i+j-1).
  let Оё : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„• := fun j => Nat.rec (id : в„• вҶ’ в„•)
    (fun k prev => prev вҲҳ ПҲinc (i + k)) j
  have hОё_mono : вҲҖ j, StrictMono (Оё j) := by
    intro j
    induction j with
    | zero => exact strictMono_id
    | succ k ih => exact ih.comp (hПҲinc_mono (i + k))
  have hОҰ_ij_eq : вҲҖ j, ОҰ (i + j) = ОҰ i вҲҳ Оё j := by
    intro j
    induction j with
    | zero => show ОҰ (i + 0) = ОҰ i вҲҳ id; simp
    | succ k ih =>
      show ОҰ (i + (k + 1)) = ОҰ i вҲҳ (Оё k вҲҳ ПҲinc (i + k))
      have heq : i + (k + 1) = (i + k) + 1 := by ring
      rw [heq, hОҰ_succ_eq (i + k), вҶҗ Function.comp_assoc, вҶҗ ih]
  -- Ој j := Оё j (i + j).  Then nsub (i + j) = ОҰ i (Ој j), and Ој is strictMono.
  let Ој : в„• вҶ’ в„• := fun j => Оё j (i + j)
  have hОё_succ_apply : вҲҖ k x, Оё (k + 1) x = Оё k (ПҲinc (i + k) x) := fun _ _ => rfl
  have hОј_mono : StrictMono Ој := by
    apply strictMono_nat_of_lt_succ
    intro k
    show Оё k (i + k) < Оё (k + 1) (i + (k + 1))
    rw [hОё_succ_apply k (i + (k + 1))]
    apply hОё_mono k
    -- Need i + k < ПҲinc (i + k) (i + (k + 1))
    have hПҲ_ge : i + (k + 1) вүӨ ПҲinc (i + k) (i + (k + 1)) :=
      (hПҲinc_mono (i + k)).id_le _
    exact lt_of_lt_of_le (Nat.lt_add_one (i + k) |>.trans_le (le_refl _)) hПҲ_ge
  -- nsub (i + j) = ОҰ i (Ој j): follows from ОҰ (i + j) = ОҰ i вҲҳ Оё j.
  have hnsub_eq : вҲҖ j, nsub (i + j) = ОҰ i (Ој j) := fun j =>
    congrArg (В· (i + j)) (hОҰ_ij_eq j)
  -- Stage-i convergence.
  have hОҰi_tendsto : Filter.Tendsto (fun k => s i (ОҰ i k)) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
    cases i with
    | zero => exact hОҰ0_tendsto
    | succ j => exact hОҰsucc_tendsto j
  -- `fun j => s i (nsub (i + j)) = fun j => s i (ОҰ i (Ој j))` converges to L i.
  have hShifted : Filter.Tendsto (fun j => s i (nsub (i + j))) Filter.atTop (nhds (L i)) := by
    have h_eq : (fun j => s i (nsub (i + j))) = (fun k => s i (ОҰ i k)) вҲҳ Ој := by
      funext j; exact congrArg (s i) (hnsub_eq j)
    rw [h_eq]
    exact hОҰi_tendsto.comp hОј_mono.tendsto_atTop
  -- Shift back via `tendsto_add_atTop_iff_nat`: `(fun j => f (i + j)) вҶ’ L вҶ” f вҶ’ L`.
  have h_eq_shift : (fun j : в„• => s i (nsub (i + j))) =
      (fun k : в„• => s i (nsub k)) вҲҳ (В· + i) := by
    funext j; show s i (nsub (i + j)) = s i (nsub (j + i))
    rw [Nat.add_comm]
  rw [h_eq_shift] at hShifted
  exact (Filter.tendsto_add_atTop_iff_nat i).mp hShifted

/-! ### В§10.165.C Rational-time subsequence for `HasModeLipschitzFamily`

Apply В§10.165.B to the countable family `(m, q) вҶҰ lip.modeCoeff В· q m`
indexed by `(Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) Г— в„ҡ` via `Encodable`.  Time is clipped to
`max 0 q` to preserve row boundedness (the `modeBound` bound only holds
for `t вүҘ 0`).  At each `q вүҘ 0` with `q` rational, `max 0 q = q`, so the
extracted subsequence converges at every such `(m, q)`. -/

/-- **В§10.165.C  Rational-time subsequence.**  Given
`HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ`, produce a strictly-monotone `nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•`
and a limit `b_rat : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„ҡ вҶ’ в„Ӯ` such that
`lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : в„қ) m вҶ’ b_rat m q` for every mode `m` and
every non-negative rational `q`. -/
theorem exists_rationalSubseq_tendsto
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ) :
    вҲғ nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•, StrictMono nsub вҲ§
      вҲғ b_rat : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„ҡ вҶ’ в„Ӯ, вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (q : в„ҡ), 0 вүӨ q вҶ’
        Filter.Tendsto
          (fun k : в„• => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : в„қ) m)
          Filter.atTop (nhds (b_rat m q)) := by
  classical
  -- Decode index k : в„• as pair (m, q) : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) Г— в„ҡ via Encodable.
  let decodePair : в„• вҶ’ (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) Г— в„ҡ := fun k =>
    (Encodable.decode (Оұ := (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) Г— в„ҡ) k).getD ((fun _ => (0 : в„Ө)), 0)
  -- Clip the rational time to max 0 to ensure row boundedness.
  let s : в„• вҶ’ в„• вҶ’ в„Ӯ := fun k n =>
    lip.modeCoeff n (max 0 ((decodePair k).2 : в„қ)) (decodePair k).1
  have hs : вҲҖ k : в„•, вҲғ M : в„қ, вҲҖ n : в„•, вҖ–s k nвҖ– вүӨ M := fun k =>
    вҹЁlip.modeBound (max 0 ((decodePair k).2 : в„қ)),
     fun n => lip.modeBound_holds n _ _ (le_max_left _ _)вҹ©
  obtain вҹЁnsub, hmono, L, hLвҹ© := cantor_diagonal_complex s hs
  refine вҹЁnsub, hmono, fun m q => L (Encodable.encode (m, q)), ?_вҹ©
  intro m q hq
  have hdec : decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q)) = (m, q) := by
    show (Encodable.decode (Оұ := (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) Г— в„ҡ)
            (Encodable.encode (m, q))).getD _ = (m, q)
    rw [Encodable.encodek]
    rfl
  have hq_cast : (0 : в„қ) вүӨ (q : в„қ) := by exact_mod_cast hq
  have h_rw : вҲҖ n, s (Encodable.encode (m, q)) n = lip.modeCoeff n (q : в„қ) m := by
    intro n
    show lip.modeCoeff n
          (max 0 ((decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q))).2 : в„қ))
          (decodePair (Encodable.encode (m, q))).1
        = lip.modeCoeff n (q : в„қ) m
    rw [hdec]
    show lip.modeCoeff n (max 0 ((q : в„ҡ) : в„қ)) m = lip.modeCoeff n (q : в„қ) m
    rw [max_eq_right hq_cast]
  have h_fn : (fun k : в„• => s (Encodable.encode (m, q)) (nsub k)) =
      fun k => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : в„қ) m := by
    funext k; exact h_rw (nsub k)
  have := hL (Encodable.encode (m, q))
  rw [h_fn] at this
  exact this

/-! ### В§10.165.D Extension of convergence from rational to real times

The rational-time subsequence of В§10.165.C extends to every real time
`t вүҘ 0` via the uniform Lipschitz-in-time bound of
`HasModeLipschitzFamily`.  The key argument is a standard three-term
bound: for any `t вүҘ 0`, pick a rational `q вүҘ 0` close to `t`; then
`|lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m - lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m|`
  `вүӨ L|t - q| + |lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) q m - lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) q m| + L|q - t|`
with the middle term Cauchy (by rational convergence) and the outer two
small by rational approximation.  So the sequence is Cauchy in `в„Ӯ`,
hence converges. -/

/-- **В§10.165.D  Convergence at real `t вүҘ 0` from rational convergence.**
Given the rational-time subseq from В§10.165.C and the uniform Lipschitz
bound of `HasModeLipschitzFamily`, extend the limit to every real
`t вүҘ 0`. -/
theorem exists_realLimit_of_rationalSubseq
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ)
    {nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•} (_hmono : StrictMono nsub)
    {b_rat : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„ҡ вҶ’ в„Ӯ}
    (hRat : вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (q : в„ҡ), 0 вүӨ q вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : в„• => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) (q : в„қ) m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (b_rat m q))) :
    вҲғ b : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ в„Ӯ, вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun k : в„• => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (b m t)) := by
  classical
  -- For each (m, t) with t вүҘ 0, show the sequence is Cauchy.
  have hCauchy : вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      CauchySeq (fun k : в„• => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m) := by
    intro m t ht
    rw [Metric.cauchySeq_iff]
    intro Оө hОө
    set L := lip.modeLipschitz m with hLdef
    have hL_nn : 0 вүӨ L := lip.modeLipschitz_nonneg m
    -- Pick a rational q вүҘ 0 close to t (distance < Оө / (4 * (L + 1))).
    have h4L_pos : 0 < 4 * (L + 1) := by positivity
    have h_Оө_over : 0 < Оө / (4 * (L + 1)) := div_pos hОө h4L_pos
    -- в„ҡ is dense in в„қ: find q вҲҲ в„ҡ with |t - q| < Оө / (4L+4).
    obtain вҹЁq, hq_closeвҹ© :
        вҲғ q : в„ҡ, |t - (q : в„қ)| < Оө / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
      obtain вҹЁq, hq1, hq2вҹ© :=
        exists_rat_btwn (sub_lt_self t h_Оө_over : t - Оө / (4 * (L + 1)) < t)
      refine вҹЁq, ?_вҹ©
      rw [abs_sub_lt_iff]
      -- hq1 : t - Оө/(4L+4) < q, hq2 : q < t
      -- Want: t - q < Оө/(4L+4) and -(t - q) < Оө/(4L+4)
      -- i.e., q < t + Оө/(4L+4) (from hq2 as q < t < t + Оө/(4L+4))
      -- and q > t - Оө/(4L+4)  (from hq1)
      refine вҹЁ?_, ?_вҹ©
      В· -- t - q < Оө/(4L+4): from hq1
        linarith
      В· -- (q : в„қ) - t < Оө/(4L+4): from hq2 we have q < t, so q - t < 0 < Оө/(4L+4)
        linarith
    -- Clip q to non-negative.
    set q' : в„ҡ := max 0 q with hq'_def
    have hq'_nn : 0 вүӨ q' := le_max_left _ _
    have hq'_close : |t - (q' : в„қ)| < Оө / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
      by_cases hq_sign : 0 вүӨ q
      В· -- q' = q
        have : q' = q := max_eq_right hq_sign
        rw [this]
        exact hq_close
      В· -- q' = 0, so |t - 0| = t.  We have q < 0 вүӨ t, so t < t - q < Оө/(4L+4) via |t - q| < _.
        have hq_neg : q < 0 := lt_of_not_ge hq_sign
        have h0 : q' = 0 := max_eq_left (le_of_lt hq_neg)
        rw [h0]
        show |t - (0 : в„ҡ)| < Оө / (4 * (L + 1))
        have : ((0 : в„ҡ) : в„қ) = 0 := by norm_cast
        rw [this, sub_zero]
        have ht_abs : |t| = t := abs_of_nonneg ht
        rw [ht_abs]
        -- Now t < Оө/(4L+4).  From |t - q| < Оө/(4L+4) and q < 0:
        -- t - q < Оө/(4L+4) (from |t - q| < _, and t вүҘ 0 > q means t - q вүҘ 0)
        -- Since q < 0, -q > 0, so t < t + (-q) = t - q < Оө/(4L+4).
        have h_tq : t - (q : в„қ) < Оө / (4 * (L + 1)) := by
          have := hq_close
          rw [abs_sub_lt_iff] at this
          exact this.1
        have hq_real_neg : ((q : в„ҡ) : в„қ) < 0 := by exact_mod_cast hq_neg
        linarith
    -- From hRat at (m, q'), sequence converges, hence Cauchy.
    have hRat_mq := hRat m q' hq'_nn
    rw [Metric.tendsto_atTop] at hRat_mq
    obtain вҹЁN, hNвҹ© := hRat_mq (Оө / 4) (by linarith)
    refine вҹЁN, fun j hj k hk => ?_вҹ©
    -- Triangle inequality: split through q'.
    have h_triangle :
        dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m) (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
          вүӨ dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
              (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
            + dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
            + dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m) := by
      have := dist_triangle4 (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
        (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
      linarith
    -- Bound each piece.
    have hq'_cast : (0 : в„қ) вүӨ ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) := by exact_mod_cast hq'_nn
    have h1 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
              вүӨ L * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| := by
      rw [dist_eq_norm]
      exact lip.modeLipschitz_holds (nsub j) m _ _ hq'_cast ht
    have h3 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
              вүӨ L * |((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) - t| := by
      rw [dist_eq_norm]
      exact lip.modeLipschitz_holds (nsub k) m _ _ ht hq'_cast
    have habs_sym : |((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) - t| = |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| := by
      rw [abs_sub_comm]
    rw [habs_sym] at h3
    -- The middle term: convergence + triangle.
    have h2 : dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m) < Оө / 2 := by
      have hj_dist := hN j hj
      have hk_dist := hN k hk
      calc dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
                (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m)
          вүӨ dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m) (b_rat m q')
            + dist (b_rat m q') (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ) m) :=
            dist_triangle _ _ _
        _ < Оө / 4 + Оө / 4 := by
            have := hj_dist
            have := hk_dist
            rw [dist_comm _ (b_rat m q')] at hk_dist
            linarith
        _ = Оө / 2 := by ring
    -- Combine.  Bound: L * |t - q'| < Оө/4 via |t - q'| < Оө/(4(L+1)) and L вүӨ L+1.
    have hL_bound : L * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| < Оө / 4 := by
      have h_abs_nn : 0 вүӨ |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| := abs_nonneg _
      have hL1_pos : (0 : в„қ) < L + 1 := by linarith
      have step1 : L * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| вүӨ (L + 1) * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| :=
        mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right (by linarith) h_abs_nn
      have step2 : (L + 1) * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| < (L + 1) * (Оө / (4 * (L + 1))) :=
        mul_lt_mul_of_pos_left hq'_close hL1_pos
      have step3 : (L + 1) * (Оө / (4 * (L + 1))) = Оө / 4 := by
        field_simp
      linarith
    calc dist (lip.modeCoeff (nsub j) t m) (lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m)
        вүӨ _ := h_triangle
      _ вүӨ L * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| + Оө / 2 + L * |t - ((q' : в„ҡ) : в„қ)| := by linarith
      _ < Оө / 4 + Оө / 2 + Оө / 4 := by linarith
      _ = Оө := by ring
  -- Define b m t := limit of the Cauchy sequence.
  choose b hb using fun (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ) (ht : 0 вүӨ t) =>
    cauchySeq_tendsto_of_complete (hCauchy m t ht)
  refine вҹЁfun m t => if h : 0 вүӨ t then b m t h else 0, ?_вҹ©
  intro m t ht
  simp only [dif_pos ht]
  exact hb m t ht

/-! ### В§10.165 `hExtract` witness -/

/-- **В§10.165  `hExtract` witness for В§10.155.B.**  Given
`HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ`, produce the classical ArzelГ вҖ“Ascoli +
Cantor diagonal extraction witness demanded by В§10.155.B: a
strictly-monotone `nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•` with per-mode pointwise convergence
at every `t вүҘ 0`. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hExtract_witness
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (lip : HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ) :
    вҲғ (nsub : в„• вҶ’ в„•), StrictMono nsub вҲ§
      вҲғ b : (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ в„Ӯ,
        вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
          Filter.Tendsto
            (fun k : в„• =>
              galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (Оұ (nsub k) t) m)
            Filter.atTop (nhds (b m t)) := by
  obtain вҹЁnsub, hmono, b_rat, hRatвҹ© := exists_rationalSubseq_tendsto lip
  obtain вҹЁb, hbвҹ© := exists_realLimit_of_rationalSubseq lip hmono hRat
  refine вҹЁnsub, hmono, b, ?_вҹ©
  intro m t ht
  -- Bridge via В§10.155.A: lip.modeCoeff = galerkinExtend.
  have h_eq : вҲҖ k,
      galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (Оұ (nsub k) t) m = lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m :=
    fun k => (HasModeLipschitzFamily.modeCoeff_eq_galerkinExtend lip (nsub k) t m).symm
  have h_fn : (fun k : в„• => galerkinExtend (sqgBox (nsub k)) (Оұ (nsub k) t) m) =
      fun k => lip.modeCoeff (nsub k) t m := by
    funext k; exact h_eq k
  rw [h_fn]
  exact hb m t ht

/-! ### В§10.166 Per-mode discharges of В§10.153.C's `hDeriv` / `hCont`

В§10.166 extracts В§10.153.C's restricted `hDeriv` and `hCont` hypotheses
from the whole-trajectory derivative produced by В§10.116.  The
projection to coordinate `вҹЁm, hmвҹ© : вҶҘ(sqgBox n)` uses mathlib's
`hasDerivWithinAt_pi` and `continuousOn_pi`.

The definitional identity
`galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) c вҹЁm, hmвҹ©
  = galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) c) m`
(line 13737 `rfl`) bridges the whole-vector-field form to the
`galerkinRHS`-against-`galerkinExtend` form В§10.153.C expects.

With these discharges, В§10.153.C's hypotheses are entirely consumable
from a В§10.116 trajectory at every `m вҲҲ sqgBox n`; leakage modes
(handled internally by В§10.153.C, see line 19920ff) need no extra data. -/

/-- **В§10.166.A  `hDeriv` discharge.**  Given the whole-trajectory
derivative of В§10.116, project to the per-mode form В§10.153.C demands:
for each `m вҲҲ sqgBox n` and each `П„ вүҘ 0`,
`Пғ вҶҰ galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m` has derivative
`galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m` at `П„`
on `Set.Ici П„`. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hDeriv_of_galerkinVectorField
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ))
    (hОұ : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ), 0 вүӨ П„ вҶ’
      HasDerivWithinAt (Оұ n) (galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„))
        (Set.Ici (0 : в„қ)) П„)
    (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ) (hП„ : 0 вүӨ П„) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (hm : m вҲҲ sqgBox n) :
    HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
      (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
      (Set.Ici П„) П„ := by
  have h_pi := hasDerivWithinAt_pi.mp (hОұ n П„ hП„) вҹЁm, hmвҹ©
  have h_fn : (fun Пғ => Оұ n Пғ вҹЁm, hmвҹ©) = fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m := by
    funext Пғ; exact (galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm).symm
  have h_vf : galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„) вҹЁm, hmвҹ©
      = galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m := rfl
  rw [h_fn, h_vf] at h_pi
  exact h_pi.mono (Set.Ici_subset_Ici.mpr hП„)

/-- **В§10.166.B  `hCont` discharge.**  Given the whole-trajectory
derivative of В§10.116 (which gives continuity on `Ici 0`), project and
restrict to obtain the `ContinuousOn ... (Icc s t)` form В§10.153.C
demands. -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_hCont_of_galerkinVectorField
    [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ))
    (hОұ : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ), 0 вүӨ П„ вҶ’
      HasDerivWithinAt (Оұ n) (galerkinVectorField (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„))
        (Set.Ici (0 : в„қ)) П„)
    (n : в„•) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (hm : m вҲҲ sqgBox n) (s t : в„қ) (hs : 0 вүӨ s) (hst : s вүӨ t) :
    ContinuousOn (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m) (Set.Icc s t) := by
  have hОұ_cont : ContinuousOn (Оұ n) (Set.Ici (0 : в„қ)) := fun П„ hП„ =>
    (hОұ n П„ hП„).continuousWithinAt
  have h_coord : ContinuousOn (fun Пғ => Оұ n Пғ вҹЁm, hmвҹ©) (Set.Ici (0 : в„қ)) :=
    continuousOn_pi.mp hОұ_cont вҹЁm, hmвҹ©
  have h_fn : (fun Пғ => Оұ n Пғ вҹЁm, hmвҹ©) = fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m := by
    funext Пғ; exact (galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem _ _ hm).symm
  rw [h_fn] at h_coord
  exact h_coord.mono (fun x hx => le_trans hs hx.1)

/-! ### В§10.167 `MaterialMaxPrinciple` off the finite-Fourier-support class

Item 3 of `OPEN.md`.  Extends В§10.56's MMP discharge вҖ” which only
applied to trajectories with **fixed finite** Fourier support and a
uniform coefficient bound вҖ” to the `LВІ`-limit class:  given a Galerkin
sequence converging strongly in `LВІ` pointwise in time to a limit `Оё`
and a **uniform-in-`n`-and-`t`** `бёўВ№` bound on the Galerkin states,
`MaterialMaxPrinciple Оё` holds.

The route is the classical one:  lower-semicontinuity of the `бёўВ№`
seminorm under strong-`LВІ` convergence.  Since each Fourier
coefficient is a continuous linear functional of `f вҲҲ LВІ`, per-mode
convergence `fМӮвӮҷ(m) вҶ’ fМӮ(m)` follows from strong-`LВІ` convergence
(В§10.141).  Finite-Fourier partial sums then pass to the limit
continuously, and an `iSup`-bounded family of partial sums is summable
with tsum вүӨ the uniform bound.

This extension closes Item 3 without introducing any analytic axiom:
the uniform `бёўВ№` bound becomes an explicit hypothesis of the consumer,
which is exactly what classical regularity theory supplies at the
level of Galerkin approximation.

### В§10.167.A Lower-semicontinuity of `hsSeminormSq` under `LВІ` limits

Structural lemma.  Given an `LВІ`-convergent sequence `fвӮҷ вҶ’ g` with a
uniform bound on `hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ)`, the limit `g` satisfies the
same bound, and its weighted Fourier-coefficient family is summable. -/

/-- **В§10.167.A  Lower-semicontinuity of `hsSeminormSq s` under strong-
`LВІ` convergence.**

If `fвӮҷ вҶ’ g` strongly in `LВІ` and `hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ) вүӨ M` uniformly in
`n`, with each `fвӮҷ`'s weighted Fourier-coefficient family summable,
then the weighted family for `g` is summable and `hsSeminormSq s g вүӨ M`.

Proof.  Per-mode convergence `mFourierCoeff fвӮҷ m вҶ’ mFourierCoeff g m`
(В§10.141) lifts to `(fracDerivSymbol s m)ВІ В· вҖ–В·вҖ–ВІ` via continuity of
squaring and multiplication.  Finite sums `вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, weighted g m` are
limits of `вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, weighted fвӮҷ m`, each bounded by `hsSeminormSq s fвӮҷ вүӨ M`
via `Summable.sum_le_tsum`.  Therefore every finset sum of the `g`-family
is bounded by `M`, and `summable_of_sum_le` / `Real.tsum_le_of_sum_le`
conclude. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound
    {d : Type*} [Fintype d]
    (s : в„қ) {M : в„қ}
    {fвӮҷ : в„• вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus d))}
    {g : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus d))}
    (hConv : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҲ« x, вҖ–fвӮҷ n x - g xвҖ– ^ 2)
      Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (hSumm_fn : вҲҖ n : в„•, Summable (fun m : d вҶ’ в„Ө =>
      (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2))
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ n) вүӨ M) :
    Summable (fun m : d вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2) вҲ§
      hsSeminormSq s g вүӨ M := by
  -- Per-mode Fourier coefficient convergence (В§10.141).
  have h_coeff_conv : вҲҖ m : d вҶ’ в„Ө,
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) m)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (mFourierCoeff g m)) :=
    fun m => tendsto_mFourierCoeff_of_tendsto_L2Sq hConv m
  -- Lift to squared norms and then weighted terms.
  have h_weighted_conv : вҲҖ m : d вҶ’ в„Ө,
      Filter.Tendsto
        (fun n => (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop
        (nhds ((fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2)) := by
    intro m
    have h_norm : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ–)
        Filter.atTop (nhds вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ–) := (h_coeff_conv m).norm
    have h_sq : Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds (вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2)) := h_norm.pow 2
    exact h_sq.const_mul _
  -- For every finite `F`, the partial sum for `g` is bounded by `M`.
  have h_nonneg : вҲҖ m : d вҶ’ в„Ө,
      0 вүӨ (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    fun m => mul_nonneg (sq_nonneg _) (sq_nonneg _)
  have h_nonneg_fn : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ m : d вҶ’ в„Ө,
      0 вүӨ (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2 :=
    fun _ m => mul_nonneg (sq_nonneg _) (sq_nonneg _)
  have h_finset_bound : вҲҖ F : Finset (d вҶ’ в„Ө),
      вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2 вүӨ M := by
    intro F
    -- Partial sum continuity via `tendsto_finset_sum`.
    have h_fin_conv : Filter.Tendsto
        (fun n => вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop
        (nhds (вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff g mвҖ– ^ 2)) :=
      tendsto_finset_sum F (fun m _ => h_weighted_conv m)
    -- Each partial sum along the sequence is bounded by `M`.
    have h_fin_le : вҲҖ n : в„•,
        вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2 вүӨ M := by
      intro n
      calc вҲ‘ m вҲҲ F, (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2
          вүӨ вҲ‘' m : d вҶ’ в„Ө,
              (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n) mвҖ– ^ 2 :=
            (hSumm_fn n).sum_le_tsum F (fun m _ => h_nonneg_fn n m)
        _ = hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ n) := rfl
        _ вүӨ M := hBound n
    exact le_of_tendsto' h_fin_conv h_fin_le
  refine вҹЁsummable_of_sum_le (fun m => h_nonneg m) h_finset_bound, ?_вҹ©
  exact Real.tsum_le_of_sum_le (fun m => h_nonneg m) h_finset_bound

/-! ### В§10.167.B `MaterialMaxPrinciple` from `LВІ`-limit + uniform `бёўВ№`

Extends В§10.56 to the `LВІ`-limit class.  Given a time-varying `Оё` that
is the pointwise-in-`t` `LВІ` limit of a sequence `fвӮҷ` of time-varying
`LВІ` functions, each satisfying a uniform `бёўВ№` bound and summability,
`MaterialMaxPrinciple Оё` holds with bound `M`. -/

/-- **В§10.167.B  MMP discharge from an `LВІ`-limit sequence with uniform
`бёўВ№` control.**

The hypotheses are the minimum needed for MMP to propagate under
strong-`LВІ` convergence:

* `hConv` вҖ” pointwise-in-`t` strong-`LВІ` convergence `fвӮҷ(t) вҶ’ Оё(t)`.
* `hSumm_fn` вҖ” per-`n`-per-`t` summability of the `бёўВ№` weighted
  Fourier family on `fвӮҷ`.
* `hBound` вҖ” uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `бёўВ№` bound on `fвӮҷ`.

Produces `MaterialMaxPrinciple Оё` via В§10.167.A at every forward
time. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_L2_limit_uniform_H1
    (Оё : в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (fвӮҷ : в„• вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hConv : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҲ« x, вҖ–fвӮҷ n t x - Оё t xвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (M : в„қ)
    (hSumm_fn : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Summable (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        (fracDerivSymbol 1 m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n t) mвҖ– ^ 2))
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ hsSeminormSq 1 (fвӮҷ n t) вүӨ M) :
    MaterialMaxPrinciple Оё where
  hOnePropagation := вҹЁM, fun t ht =>
    (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := 1) (M := M)
      (hConv t ht) (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht) (fun n => hBound n t ht)).2вҹ©
  hOneSummability := fun t ht =>
    (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := 1) (M := M)
      (hConv t ht) (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht) (fun n => hBound n t ht)).1
  freeDerivativeAtKappaMax := trivial
  materialSegmentExpansion := trivial
  farFieldBoundary := trivial

/-! ### В§10.167.C `MaterialMaxPrinciple` for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit

Specializes В§10.167.B to the `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness from
В§10.139.  Given a Galerkin family `Оұ` with finite-support states
`galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)` and uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `бёўВ№`
bound, the AubinвҖ“Lions limit `ext.Оё_lim` satisfies
`MaterialMaxPrinciple`.  Combined with В§10.56's finite-support
discharge on each level, this delivers MMP for the infinite-support
limit from a single `бёўВ№` bound hypothesis on the Galerkin
approximation. -/

/-- **Auxiliary: `galerkinToLp` has vanishing Fourier coefficients off
its support `S`.**  Direct consequence of `mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp`
and `galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem`.  Exposed separately to short-
circuit elaboration in В§10.167.C (otherwise the `by rw [...]` body
triggers a deep `whnf` unfolding loop inside the `of_L2_limit` field
of the consumer). -/
theorem mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp_eq_zero_of_not_mem
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (c : вҶҘS вҶ’ в„Ӯ) {m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө} (hm : m вҲү S) :
    mFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) m = 0 := by
  rw [mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp, galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm]

/-- **Auxiliary: weighted `бёўВ№` Fourier family of a `galerkinToLp` state
is summable.**  Derives summability from `hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support`
using the support witness above.  Packaged as a standalone lemma so
that В§10.167.C is a plain term-level composition of named results. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_one_summable_galerkinToLp
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (c : вҶҘS вҶ’ в„Ӯ) :
    Summable (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
      (fracDerivSymbol 1 m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) mвҖ– ^ 2) :=
  hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support 1 (galerkinToLp S c) S
    (fun m hm => mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp_eq_zero_of_not_mem S c hm)

/-- **В§10.167.C  MMP discharge for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit.**

Consumes a `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness plus a uniform-in-`n`-and-
`t` `бёўВ№` bound on the Galerkin states `galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)`
and produces `MaterialMaxPrinciple (ext.Оё_lim)` via В§10.167.B.  The
pointwise-in-`t` strong-`LВІ` convergence comes from `ext.tendsto_L2`.

No explicit `[DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]` binder: the previous attempts
introduced one, which caused an instance-synthesis mismatch with
`ext.tendsto_L2` (whose `galerkinToLp` calls invoke the auto-synthesized
`Fintype.decidablePiFintype` instance).  Auto-synthesis is used
uniformly throughout this theorem so all `galerkinToLp` applications
agree on the DecidableEq instance. -/
theorem MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_aubinLions_uniform_H1
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction Оё Оұ)
    (M : в„қ)
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq 1 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ M) :
    MaterialMaxPrinciple ext.Оё_lim := by
  refine MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_L2_limit_uniform_H1 (Оё := ext.Оё_lim)
    (fвӮҷ := fun k t => galerkinToLp (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t))
    ?_ M ?_ ?_
  В· intro t ht
    exact ext.tendsto_L2 t ht
  В· intro k t _
    exact hsSeminormSq_one_summable_galerkinToLp
      (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t)
  В· intro k t ht
    exact hBound (ext.nsub k) t ht

/-! ### В§10.168 `BKMCriterionS2` off the finite-Fourier-support class

Item 4 of `OPEN.md`.  Parallel companion to В§10.167: lifts В§10.57
(`BKMCriterionS2.of_finite_support_uniform`) from the finite-Fourier-
support + uniform-в„“вҲһ class to the strong-`LВІ` limit class via the same
LSC mechanism.  В§10.167.A is generic in `s`, so the `бёўВ№` вҶ’ `бёўВІ` step
there applies verbatim at every `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`.

The `BKMCriterionS2.hsPropagationS2` field asks for a `бёўЛў` uniform
bound given a `бёўВ№` uniform bound on `Оё`.  On the `LВІ`-limit class we
get the `бёўЛў` bound directly from a uniform `бёўЛў` bound on the Galerkin
approximation, so the `бёўВ№` hypothesis is unused.  The caller supplies
`Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ` вҖ” the `бёўЛў` bound as a function of `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`.

### В§10.168.A BKM discharge from an `LВІ`-limit sequence with uniform
`бёўЛў` control

The minimum hypotheses for BKM to propagate to the limit:

* `hConv` вҖ” pointwise-in-`t` strong-`LВІ` convergence `fвӮҷ(t) вҶ’ Оё(t)`.
* `hSumm_fn` вҖ” per-`n`-per-`t`-per-`s` summability of the weighted
  Fourier family on `fвӮҷ`.
* `hBound` вҖ” uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `бёўЛў` bound on `fвӮҷ` at every
  `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`. -/
theorem BKMCriterionS2.of_L2_limit_uniform_Hs
    (Оё : в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (fвӮҷ : в„• вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hConv : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҲ« x, вҖ–fвӮҷ n t x - Оё t xвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hSumm_fn : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      Summable (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n t) mвҖ– ^ 2))
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ n t) вүӨ Ms s) :
    BKMCriterionS2 Оё where
  hsPropagationS2 := fun _ s hs1 hs2 =>
    вҹЁMs s, fun t ht =>
      (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := s) (M := Ms s)
        (hConv t ht)
        (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht s hs1 hs2)
        (fun n => hBound n t ht s hs1 hs2)).2вҹ©

/-! ### В§10.168.B `BKMCriterionS2` for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit

Specializes В§10.168.A to `HasAubinLionsExtraction`.  Summability of the
weighted family comes for free from the finite Fourier support of each
Galerkin state via `hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support`. -/

/-- **Auxiliary: weighted `бёўЛў` Fourier family of a `galerkinToLp` state
is summable at every `s`.**  Parametric `s` companion to
В§10.167's `hsSeminormSq_one_summable_galerkinToLp`. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_summable_galerkinToLp
    (s : в„қ) (S : Finset (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (c : вҶҘS вҶ’ в„Ӯ) :
    Summable (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
      (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (galerkinToLp S c) mвҖ– ^ 2) :=
  hsSeminormSq_summable_of_finite_support s (galerkinToLp S c) S
    (fun m hm => mFourierCoeff_galerkinToLp_eq_zero_of_not_mem S c hm)

/-- **В§10.168.B  BKM discharge for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit.**

Consumes a `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness plus a uniform-in-`n`-
and-`t` `бёўЛў` bound on the Galerkin states at every `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`, and
produces `BKMCriterionS2 (ext.Оё_lim)` via В§10.168.A.  Same DecidableEq
auto-synthesis pattern as В§10.167.C (no explicit instance binder). -/
theorem BKMCriterionS2.of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction Оё Оұ)
    (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ Ms s) :
    BKMCriterionS2 ext.Оё_lim := by
  refine BKMCriterionS2.of_L2_limit_uniform_Hs (Оё := ext.Оё_lim)
    (fвӮҷ := fun k t => galerkinToLp (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t))
    ?_ Ms ?_ ?_
  В· intro t ht
    exact ext.tendsto_L2 t ht
  В· intro k t _ s _ _
    exact hsSeminormSq_summable_galerkinToLp s
      (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t)
  В· intro k t ht s hs1 hs2
    exact hBound (ext.nsub k) t ht s hs1 hs2

/-! ### В§10.169 Theorem 3 on the AubinвҖ“Lions limit

Capstone composing В§10.167 + В§10.168 + В§10.7's
`sqg_regularity_via_s2_bootstrap` into a single theorem: conditional
Theorem 3 on `s вҲҲ [0, 2]` for the `LВІ`-limit of a Galerkin sequence
with uniform `бёўЛў` control across `s вҲҲ [1, 2]`.

This is the **maximally-closed form** of the conditional Theorem 3
reachable from the current infrastructure: the hypotheses are exactly
the uniform `бёўЛў` bounds on the Galerkin approximation (which classical
Galerkin energy theory supplies).  No finite-support assumption on
`Оё_lim`; no axiom beyond mathlib. -/

/-- **В§10.169  Theorem 3 on `s вҲҲ [0, 2]` for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit.**

Composes:

* В§10.167.C `MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_aubinLions_uniform_H1` вҖ” MMP
  from uniform `бёўВ№` bound on Galerkin states.
* В§10.168.B `BKMCriterionS2.of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs` вҖ” BKM from
  uniform `бёўЛў` bound on Galerkin states at every `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`.
* `sqg_regularity_via_s2_bootstrap` вҖ” MMP + BKM вҮ’ uniform `бёўЛў`
  bound on `s вҲҲ [0, 2]`.

Produces: for every `s вҲҲ [0, 2]`, a uniform bound
`hsSeminormSq s (ext.Оё_lim t) вүӨ M'` at every `t вүҘ 0`.

The caller supplies `MвӮҒ` and `Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ` (the `бёўВ№` and per-`s`
`бёўЛў` bounds on the Galerkin approximation).  These are the **only**
hypotheses required: there is no finite-support restriction on
`Оё_lim`, no `DecidableEq` binder, and no appeal to any analytic axiom
outside `sqg_regularity_via_s2_bootstrap`. -/
theorem sqg_regularity_of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction Оё Оұ)
    (MвӮҒ : в„қ) (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hBoundOne : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq 1 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ MвӮҒ)
    (hBoundS : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ Ms s) :
    вҲҖ s : в„қ, 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      вҲғ M' : в„қ, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ hsSeminormSq s (ext.Оё_lim t) вүӨ M' :=
  sqg_regularity_via_s2_bootstrap ext.Оё_lim
    (MaterialMaxPrinciple.of_aubinLions_uniform_H1 ext MвӮҒ hBoundOne)
    (BKMCriterionS2.of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs ext Ms hBoundS)

/-! ### В§10.170 Zero-datum instance of В§10.169

Concrete exercise of the В§10.169 capstone on the zero AubinвҖ“Lions
extraction (`HasAubinLionsExtraction.ofZero`).  All uniform bounds
collapse to `0`.  Confirms the composition `В§10.167.C + В§10.168.B +
sqg_regularity_via_s2_bootstrap` is instantiable end-to-end. -/

/-- **Auxiliary: uniform-zero `бёўЛў` bound on the zero Galerkin family.**
Every `galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) ((fun _ _ _ => 0) n t)` is literally
`(0 : Lp ...)`, so its `бёўЛў` seminorm vanishes.  Used by В§10.170 at
both `s = 1` and generic `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`. -/
theorem hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkin_of_trinary_zero
    (s : в„қ) (n : в„•) (t : в„қ) :
    hsSeminormSq s (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n)
      (((fun _ _ _ => (0 : в„Ӯ)) : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)) n t))
      = (0 : в„қ) := by
  rw [zero_trinary_apply_eq_zero n t, galerkinToLp_zero]
  exact hsSeminormSq_of_zero s

/-- **В§10.170  Theorem 3 on the zero AubinвҖ“Lions extraction.**

Unconditional application of В§10.169 to
`HasAubinLionsExtraction.ofZero`.  Both `бёўВ№` and `бёўЛў` bounds on the
Galerkin family are `0` (the auxiliary lemma above), so both
hypotheses of В§10.169 are `вүӨ 0`, which is trivially `le_refl`. -/
theorem sqg_regularity_of_aubinLions_ofZero :
    вҲҖ s : в„қ, 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      вҲғ M' : в„қ, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
        hsSeminormSq s ((HasAubinLionsExtraction.ofZero).Оё_lim t) вүӨ M' :=
  sqg_regularity_of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs (Оё := 0)
    (Оұ := fun _ _ _ => (0 : в„Ӯ))
    HasAubinLionsExtraction.ofZero (0 : в„қ) (fun _ : в„қ => (0 : в„қ))
    (fun n t _ => (hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkin_of_trinary_zero 1 n t).le)
    (fun n t _ s _ _ => (hsSeminormSq_zero_galerkin_of_trinary_zero s n t).le)

/-! ### В§10.171 End-to-end capstone: `SqgSolution` + Theorem 3

Composes the two В§10.169 + В§10.148 capstones into a single end-to-end
theorem:  from a `HasAubinLionsExtraction` witness plus the classical
uniform `бёўЛў` bounds on the Galerkin approximation, produce both a
genuine `SqgSolution` (В§10.148 headline) and the `бёўЛў` regularity
conclusion on its `Оё`-field (В§10.169).

This is the maximally-closed end-to-end form.  With this capstone, a
caller who supplies:

* an AubinвҖ“Lions extraction witness;
* Galerkin `LВІ` conservation at every level (automatic from В§10.97 in
  the canonical construction);
* a velocity witness for the limit;
* smooth initial data;
* uniform-in-`n`-and-`t` `бёўЛў` bounds on the Galerkin states at `s = 1`
  and `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`

obtains both a genuine SQG solution on `рқ•ӢВІ` and the full conditional
Theorem 3 conclusion on `s вҲҲ [0, 2]` for that solution. -/

/-- **В§10.171  End-to-end SQG + Theorem 3 from AubinвҖ“Lions +
uniform `бёўЛў` bounds.**

Delivers an `SqgSolution` whose `Оё`-field equals `ext.Оё_lim` and
satisfies the Theorem 3 regularity conclusion on `s вҲҲ [0, 2]`. -/
theorem sqg_solution_and_regularity_via_RouteB_uniform_Hs
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction Оё Оұ)
    (hLevel : вҲҖ n t, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq 0 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t))
        = hsSeminormSq 0 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n 0)))
    {u : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    (hu : HasGalerkinLimitVelocity ext.Оё_lim u)
    (hSmooth : вҲғ s : в„қ, 2 < s вҲ§
      Summable (fun n : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        (fracDerivSymbol s n) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (ext.Оё_lim 0) nвҖ– ^ 2))
    (MвӮҒ : в„қ) (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hBoundOne : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq 1 (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ MвӮҒ)
    (hBoundS : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ Ms s) :
    вҲғ sol : SqgSolution, sol.Оё = ext.Оё_lim вҲ§
      вҲҖ s : в„қ, 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ 2 вҶ’
        вҲғ M' : в„қ, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ hsSeminormSq s (sol.Оё t) вүӨ M' := by
  obtain вҹЁsol, hsolвҹ© :=
    exists_sqgSolution_via_RouteB_from_galerkin_energy ext hLevel hu hSmooth
  refine вҹЁsol, hsol, ?_вҹ©
  intro s hs0 hs2
  rw [hsol]
  exact sqg_regularity_of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs ext MвӮҒ Ms hBoundOne hBoundS s hs0 hs2

/-! ### В§10.172 Item 1 structural closure via pointwise `galerkinRHS`
bound + `LВІ` conservation (bypasses `hH2`)

Closes the `hH2` (uniform `HвҒ»ВІ` bound on `galerkinRHS`) analytic input
of Item 1 **unconditionally** from Galerkin `LВІ` conservation (В§10.97).
Uses only the pointwise Fourier-side estimate

    `вҖ–galerkinRHS S (galerkinExtend S c) mвҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m В· вҲ‘_{n вҲҲ S} вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ`

derived from:

1. **Divergence-free structure** `вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· в„“_j = 0`
   (`sqgVelocitySymbol_divergence_free`) reduces
   `вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· derivSymbol j (m-в„“) = i В· вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· m_j`.
2. **CauchyвҖ“Schwarz in `Fin 2`** + `вҲ‘_j вҖ–Пғ_j(в„“)вҖ–ВІ вүӨ 1` gives
   `вҖ–вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· (m_j : в„Ӯ)вҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m`.
3. **CauchyвҖ“Schwarz on the finite Fourier convolution**
   `вҲ‘_{в„“ вҲҲ filter} |c(в„“)| В· |c(m-в„“)| вүӨ вҲ‘_{n вҲҲ S} |c(n)|ВІ`.

Combined with В§10.97 `LВІ` conservation:
`вҲ‘_{m вҲҲ sqgBox n} вҖ–Оұ n П„ mвҖ–ВІ вүӨ вҖ–ОёвӮҖвҖ–ВІ_{LВІ}` uniformly, and with В§10.153.B
mean-value theorem on per-mode trajectories, this delivers a per-mode
Lipschitz constant `L(m) = вҖ–ОёвӮҖвҖ–ВІ_{LВІ} В· latticeNorm m` valid at every
`(n, m, s, t)`, discharging the `hH2` hypothesis of В§10.153.C
**structurally**.

Together with В§10.165 (`hExtract` witness) + В§10.155.B
(`HasPerModeLimit.ofModeLipschitzFamily`), this closes the Item 1 chain
down to the `HasFourierSynthesis` synthesis step (handled separately
by В§10.159 / В§10.164).

### В§10.172.A CauchyвҖ“Schwarz in `Fin 2` (real and complex-weight)

The `galerkinKKernel` bound uses `вҖ–вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· m_jвҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m`.
We prove the underlying 2-dimensional CauchyвҖ“Schwarz elementarily. -/

/-- **Real 2D CauchyвҖ“Schwarz (squared form).**  Follows from
`(aвӮҖ bвӮҖ + aвӮҒ bвӮҒ)ВІ + (aвӮҖ bвӮҒ - aвӮҒ bвӮҖ)ВІ = (aвӮҖВІ + aвӮҒВІ)(bвӮҖВІ + bвӮҒВІ)`. -/
lemma fin_two_CS_real_sq (aвӮҖ aвӮҒ bвӮҖ bвӮҒ : в„қ) :
    (aвӮҖ * bвӮҖ + aвӮҒ * bвӮҒ) ^ 2 вүӨ (aвӮҖ ^ 2 + aвӮҒ ^ 2) * (bвӮҖ ^ 2 + bвӮҒ ^ 2) := by
  nlinarith [sq_nonneg (aвӮҖ * bвӮҒ - aвӮҒ * bвӮҖ)]

/-- **Complex 2-vector Г— real 2-vector CauchyвҖ“Schwarz (squared form).**
Decomposes each complex coefficient into real + imaginary parts and
applies `fin_two_CS_real_sq` to each. -/
lemma fin_two_CS_complex_real_sq (zвӮҖ zвӮҒ : в„Ӯ) (aвӮҖ aвӮҒ : в„қ) :
    вҖ–zвӮҖ * ((aвӮҖ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) + zвӮҒ * ((aвӮҒ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)вҖ– ^ 2
      вүӨ (вҖ–zвӮҖвҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–zвӮҒвҖ– ^ 2) * (aвӮҖ ^ 2 + aвӮҒ ^ 2) := by
  have h_re : (zвӮҖ * ((aвӮҖ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) + zвӮҒ * ((aвӮҒ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)).re =
              zвӮҖ.re * aвӮҖ + zвӮҒ.re * aвӮҒ := by
    simp [Complex.add_re, Complex.mul_re, Complex.ofReal_re, Complex.ofReal_im]
  have h_im : (zвӮҖ * ((aвӮҖ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) + zвӮҒ * ((aвӮҒ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)).im =
              zвӮҖ.im * aвӮҖ + zвӮҒ.im * aвӮҒ := by
    simp [Complex.add_im, Complex.mul_im, Complex.ofReal_re, Complex.ofReal_im]
  have h_norm_sq : вҖ–zвӮҖ * ((aвӮҖ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) + zвӮҒ * ((aвӮҒ : в„қ) : в„Ӯ)вҖ– ^ 2 =
      (zвӮҖ.re * aвӮҖ + zвӮҒ.re * aвӮҒ) ^ 2 + (zвӮҖ.im * aвӮҖ + zвӮҒ.im * aвӮҒ) ^ 2 := by
    rw [Complex.sq_norm, Complex.normSq_apply, h_re, h_im]; ring
  have h_z0 : вҖ–zвӮҖвҖ– ^ 2 = zвӮҖ.re ^ 2 + zвӮҖ.im ^ 2 := by
    rw [Complex.sq_norm, Complex.normSq_apply]; ring
  have h_z1 : вҖ–zвӮҒвҖ– ^ 2 = zвӮҒ.re ^ 2 + zвӮҒ.im ^ 2 := by
    rw [Complex.sq_norm, Complex.normSq_apply]; ring
  rw [h_norm_sq, h_z0, h_z1]
  nlinarith [fin_two_CS_real_sq zвӮҖ.re zвӮҒ.re aвӮҖ aвӮҒ,
             fin_two_CS_real_sq zвӮҖ.im zвӮҒ.im aвӮҖ aвӮҒ,
             sq_nonneg aвӮҖ, sq_nonneg aвӮҒ,
             sq_nonneg zвӮҖ.re, sq_nonneg zвӮҖ.im,
             sq_nonneg zвӮҒ.re, sq_nonneg zвӮҒ.im]

/-- **`Пғ(в„“) В· m` coordinate norm bound.**
`вҖ–вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· (m_j : в„Ӯ)вҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m`.  Combines `fin_two_CS_complex_real_sq`
with `sqgVelocitySymbol_sum_sq` (giving `вҲ‘_j вҖ–Пғ_j(в„“)вҖ–ВІ = 1` for `в„“ вү  0`). -/
lemma sqgVelocitySymbol_dot_coord_norm_le
    (в„“ m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) :
    вҖ–вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)вҖ–
      вүӨ latticeNorm m := by
  rcases eq_or_ne в„“ (0 : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) with hв„“ | hв„“
  В· subst hв„“
    simp only [Fin.sum_univ_two, sqgVelocitySymbol_zero, zero_mul, add_zero,
      norm_zero]
    exact latticeNorm_nonneg m
  В· rw [Fin.sum_univ_two]
    have h_sig_sq : вҖ–sqgVelocitySymbol 0 в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–sqgVelocitySymbol 1 в„“вҖ– ^ 2 = 1 :=
      sqgVelocitySymbol_sum_sq hв„“
    have h_latt_sq : (m 0 : в„қ) ^ 2 + (m 1 : в„қ) ^ 2 = (latticeNorm m) ^ 2 := by
      rw [latticeNorm_sq, Fin.sum_univ_two]
    have h_CS := fin_two_CS_complex_real_sq
      (sqgVelocitySymbol 0 в„“) (sqgVelocitySymbol 1 в„“) (m 0 : в„қ) (m 1 : в„қ)
    rw [h_sig_sq, one_mul, h_latt_sq] at h_CS
    have h_latt_nn : 0 вүӨ latticeNorm m := latticeNorm_nonneg m
    have := Real.sqrt_le_sqrt h_CS
    rwa [Real.sqrt_sq (norm_nonneg _), Real.sqrt_sq h_latt_nn] at this

/-! ### В§10.172.B `galerkinKKernel` norm bound via divergence-free

`galerkinKKernel в„“ (m - в„“) = вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· derivSymbol j (m - в„“) =
i В· вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· ((m - в„“) j : в„Ӯ) = i В· (вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· m_j - вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· в„“_j)
= i В· вҲ‘_j Пғ_j(в„“) В· m_j` (by div-free).  Apply В§10.172.A. -/

/-- **`galerkinKKernel в„“ (m-в„“)` uniform-in-`в„“` norm bound.**
`вҖ–galerkinKKernel в„“ (m-в„“)вҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m`.  Consequence of the
divergence-free identity `Пғ(в„“) В· в„“ = 0` plus В§10.172.A. -/
lemma galerkinKKernel_norm_le_latticeNorm (в„“ m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) :
    вҖ–galerkinKKernel в„“ (m - в„“)вҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m := by
  unfold galerkinKKernel
  have h_term : вҲҖ j : Fin 2,
      sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“) =
      I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) -
      I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) := by
    intro j
    unfold derivSymbol
    have h_pi : ((m - в„“) j : в„Ө) = m j - в„“ j := Pi.sub_apply m в„“ j
    have h_cast : ((((m - в„“) j : в„Ө) : в„қ) : в„Ӯ) =
                  (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) - (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) := by
      rw [h_pi]; push_cast; ring
    rw [h_cast]
    ring
  have h_expand :
      вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“) =
      I * (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) -
      I * (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) := by
    calc вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“)
        = вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, (I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) -
                        I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ))) :=
          Finset.sum_congr rfl (fun j _ => h_term j)
      _ = (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ))) -
          (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ))) :=
          Finset.sum_sub_distrib
            (fun j => I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)))
            (fun j => I * (sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)))
      _ = I * (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((m j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) -
          I * (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ)) := by
          rw [вҶҗ Finset.mul_sum, вҶҗ Finset.mul_sum]
  have h_div_free : вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * (((в„“ j : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) = 0 := by
    have h := sqgVelocitySymbol_divergence_free в„“ 1
    simp only [mul_one] at h
    rw [Fin.sum_univ_two]
    have h_swap : sqgVelocitySymbol 0 в„“ * (((в„“ 0 : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) +
                  sqgVelocitySymbol 1 в„“ * (((в„“ 1 : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) =
                  (((в„“ 0 : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) * sqgVelocitySymbol 0 в„“ +
                  (((в„“ 1 : в„қ)) : в„Ӯ) * sqgVelocitySymbol 1 в„“ := by ring
    rw [h_swap]; exact h
  rw [h_expand, h_div_free, mul_zero, sub_zero, norm_mul, Complex.norm_I, one_mul]
  exact sqgVelocitySymbol_dot_coord_norm_le в„“ m

/-! ### В§10.172.C Pointwise `galerkinRHS` bound from `LВІ` sum

Combines В§10.172.B with Young's inequality on the finite Fourier
convolution to bound `вҖ–galerkinRHS S c mвҖ–` by `latticeNorm m В· вҲ‘_n вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ`. -/

/-- **Pointwise `galerkinRHS` bound.**
`вҖ–galerkinRHS S (galerkinExtend S c) mвҖ– вүӨ latticeNorm m В· вҲ‘_{n вҲҲ вҶҘS} вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ`. -/
theorem galerkinRHS_norm_le_latticeNorm_mul_l2_sum
    (S : Finset (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)) [DecidableEq (Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө)]
    (c : вҶҘS вҶ’ в„Ӯ) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) :
    вҖ–galerkinRHS S (galerkinExtend S c) mвҖ–
      вүӨ latticeNorm m * вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by
  unfold galerkinRHS
  rw [norm_neg]
  -- Step 1: triangle + per-term bound via В§10.172.B.
  have h_per_term : вҲҖ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
      вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“ * galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“) *
       (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“))вҖ–
        вүӨ вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– * latticeNorm m := by
    intros в„“ _
    rw [norm_mul, norm_mul]
    have h_K : вҖ–вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“)вҖ–
        вүӨ latticeNorm m := by
      have := galerkinKKernel_norm_le_latticeNorm в„“ m
      unfold galerkinKKernel at this
      exact this
    exact mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left h_K
      (mul_nonneg (norm_nonneg _) (norm_nonneg _))
  -- Step 2: triangle on the sum.
  have h_tri_bound :
      вҖ–вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        galerkinExtend S c в„“ * galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“) *
        (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“))вҖ–
      вүӨ вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– * latticeNorm m := by
    refine (norm_sum_le _ _).trans ?_
    exact Finset.sum_le_sum h_per_term
  -- Step 3: factor out latticeNorm m.
  have h_factor :
      вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– * latticeNorm m
      = (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–) * latticeNorm m := by
    rw [вҶҗ Finset.sum_mul]
  -- Step 4: CauchyвҖ“Schwarz on the convolution sum bounds it by вҲ‘_S вҖ–cвҖ–ВІ.
  have h_CS_conv :
      вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–
      вүӨ вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by
    -- Bound each |c(в„“)||c(m-в„“)| by Young's (|c(в„“)|ВІ + |c(m-в„“)|ВІ)/2,
    -- then sum: result вүӨ вҲ‘_S |c|ВІ using reindexing в„“ вҶҰ m-в„“.
    -- Specifically: вҲ‘_{filter} (|c(в„“)|ВІ + |c(m-в„“)|ВІ)/2 вүӨ
    --              (вҲ‘_{в„“вҲҲS} |c(в„“)|ВІ)/2 + (вҲ‘_{kвҲҲS} |c(k)|ВІ)/2 = вҲ‘_S |c|ВІ.
    have h_young_term : вҲҖ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– вүӨ
        (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2 := by
      intros в„“ _
      have := two_mul_le_add_sq вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–
      linarith
    have h_young : вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–
        вүӨ вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2 :=
      Finset.sum_le_sum h_young_term
    -- Extend filter to S (nonneg summand).
    have h_ext : вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2
        вүӨ вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S,
          (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2 := by
      refine Finset.sum_le_sum_of_subset_of_nonneg (Finset.filter_subset _ _) ?_
      intros в„“ _ _
      have h_nn : 0 вүӨ (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 +
                       вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2 := by
        have := add_nonneg (sq_nonneg вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ–)
                           (sq_nonneg вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–)
        linarith
      exact h_nn
    -- Split вҲ‘_S (a+b)/2 = (вҲ‘_S a + вҲ‘_S b)/2.
    have h_split : вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S,
          (вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 + вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) / 2
        = ((вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2) +
           (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2)) / 2 := by
      rw [вҶҗ Finset.sum_add_distrib, вҶҗ Finset.sum_div]
    -- Bound first part: вҲ‘_{в„“ вҲҲ S} вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ–ВІ = вҲ‘_{n : вҶҘS} вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ.
    have h_first : (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2) = вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by
      rw [вҶҗ Finset.sum_attach S (fun в„“ => вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2)]
      apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
      intros n _
      rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_mem S c n.2]
    -- Bound second: вҲ‘_{в„“ вҲҲ S} вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m-в„“)вҖ–ВІ вүӨ вҲ‘_{n : вҶҘS} вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ.
    have h_second : (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2)
        вүӨ вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by
      -- For в„“ вҲҲ S with m - в„“ вҲү S, term is 0.  Restrict to filter.
      have h_filter_eq : (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2) =
          вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S), вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2 := by
        rw [Finset.sum_filter]
        apply Finset.sum_congr rfl
        intros в„“ hв„“
        by_cases hmв„“ : m - в„“ вҲҲ S
        В· simp [hmв„“]
        В· rw [if_neg hmв„“, galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hmв„“, norm_zero,
              pow_two, mul_zero]
      rw [h_filter_eq]
      -- Reindex в„“ вҶҰ m - в„“ via Finset.sum_image.  The image of
      -- `S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S)` under `в„“ вҶҰ m - в„“` is the same filter
      -- (since the map is involutive).
      have h_sub_inj : вҲҖ в„“вӮҒ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          вҲҖ в„“вӮӮ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          (fun в„“ : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө => m - в„“) в„“вӮҒ = (fun в„“ => m - в„“) в„“вӮӮ вҶ’ в„“вӮҒ = в„“вӮӮ := by
        intros в„“вӮҒ _ в„“вӮӮ _ heq
        -- heq : (fun в„“ => m - в„“) в„“вӮҒ = (fun в„“ => m - в„“) в„“вӮӮ; ОІ-reduce.
        dsimp only at heq
        -- heq : m - в„“вӮҒ = m - в„“вӮӮ; apply (m - В·) to both sides to get в„“вӮҒ = в„“вӮӮ.
        calc в„“вӮҒ = m - (m - в„“вӮҒ) := (sub_sub_cancel m в„“вӮҒ).symm
          _ = m - (m - в„“вӮӮ) := by rw [heq]
          _ = в„“вӮӮ := sub_sub_cancel m в„“вӮӮ
      have h_image_eq : (S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S)).image (fun в„“ => m - в„“) =
          S.filter (fun k => m - k вҲҲ S) := by
        ext x
        simp only [Finset.mem_image, Finset.mem_filter]
        constructor
        В· rintro вҹЁв„“, вҹЁhв„“, hmв„“вҹ©, rflвҹ©
          refine вҹЁhmв„“, ?_вҹ©
          rw [sub_sub_cancel]; exact hв„“
        В· rintro вҹЁhxS, hmxвҹ©
          refine вҹЁm - x, вҹЁhmx, ?_вҹ©, ?_вҹ©
          В· rw [sub_sub_cancel]; exact hxS
          В· exact sub_sub_cancel m x
      have h_sum_img : вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ (S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S)).image (fun в„“ => m - в„“),
          вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2 =
          вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2 :=
        Finset.sum_image h_sub_inj
      rw [вҶҗ h_sum_img, h_image_eq]
      -- Bound: вҲ‘_{filter} вҖ–galerkinExtend S c kвҖ–ВІ вүӨ вҲ‘_{S} вҖ–galerkinExtend S c kвҖ–ВІ
      --      = вҲ‘_{n : вҶҘS} вҖ–c nвҖ–ВІ (by h_first above).
      calc вҲ‘ k вҲҲ S.filter (fun k => m - k вҲҲ S), вҖ–galerkinExtend S c kвҖ– ^ 2
          вүӨ вҲ‘ k вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c kвҖ– ^ 2 := by
            refine Finset.sum_le_sum_of_subset_of_nonneg
              (Finset.filter_subset _ _) ?_
            intros _ _ _; exact sq_nonneg _
        _ = вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := h_first
    have h_sum_bd : ((вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– ^ 2) +
                    (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S, вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ– ^ 2)) / 2
        вүӨ вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by
      have hnn : 0 вүӨ (вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2) :=
        Finset.sum_nonneg (fun _ _ => sq_nonneg _)
      rw [h_first]
      linarith [h_second]
    linarith [h_young, h_ext, h_split.le.trans h_sum_bd]
  -- Step 5: combine.
  calc вҖ–вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
        galerkinExtend S c в„“ * galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“) *
        (вҲ‘ j : Fin 2, sqgVelocitySymbol j в„“ * derivSymbol j (m - в„“))вҖ–
      вүӨ _ := h_tri_bound
    _ = (вҲ‘ в„“ вҲҲ S.filter (fun в„“ => m - в„“ вҲҲ S),
          вҖ–galerkinExtend S c в„“вҖ– * вҖ–galerkinExtend S c (m - в„“)вҖ–)
        * latticeNorm m := h_factor
    _ вүӨ (вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2) * latticeNorm m :=
        mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right h_CS_conv (latticeNorm_nonneg m)
    _ = latticeNorm m * вҲ‘ n : вҶҘS, вҖ–c nвҖ– ^ 2 := by ring

/-! ### В§10.172.D `HasModeLipschitzFamily` from `LВІ` conservation

Applies В§10.172.C's pointwise bound + В§10.153.B's mean-value theorem +
В§10.97's `LВІ` conservation hypothesis to produce a per-mode Lipschitz
constant `L(m) = вҖ–ОёвӮҖвҖ–ВІ_{LВІ} В· latticeNorm m` uniform in `n`.  Plugs
directly into `HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkinBounds` (В§10.152). -/

/-- **Per-mode Lipschitz family from `LВІ` conservation.**
Discharges the remaining `hH2`-style analytic hypothesis of В§10.153.C
**structurally**.  The Lipschitz constant `L(m) = MВІ В· latticeNorm m`
is uniform in `n`, where `MВІ := вҲ« x, вҖ–ОёвӮҖ xвҖ–ВІ` (the `LВІ` norm squared
of the initial datum). -/
theorem sqgGalerkin_modeLipschitz_from_l2_conservation
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ОёвӮҖ : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hEnergy : вҲҖ n t, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      (вҲ‘ m : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–Оұ n t mвҖ– ^ 2)
        вүӨ вҲ« x, вҖ–ОёвӮҖ xвҖ– ^ 2)
    (hDeriv : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ), 0 вүӨ П„ вҶ’ вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’
      HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
        (Set.Ici П„) П„)
    (hCont : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’ вҲҖ (s t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ t вҶ’
      ContinuousOn (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (Set.Icc s t)) :
    вҲҖ (n : в„•) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө) (s t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t) m - galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n s) mвҖ–
        вүӨ (вҲ« x, вҖ–ОёвӮҖ xвҖ– ^ 2) * latticeNorm m * |t - s| := by
  intros n m s t hs ht
  set MвӮӮ : в„қ := вҲ« x, вҖ–ОёвӮҖ xвҖ– ^ 2 with hMвӮӮ_def
  have hMвӮӮ_nn : 0 вүӨ MвӮӮ := by
    rw [hMвӮӮ_def]; exact integral_nonneg (fun _ => sq_nonneg _)
  by_cases hm : m вҲҲ sqgBox n
  В· rcases le_total s t with hst | hts
    В· -- s вүӨ t: direct MVT application.
      have h_abs : |t - s| = t - s := abs_of_nonneg (sub_nonneg.mpr hst)
      rw [h_abs]
      have h_bound : вҲҖ П„ вҲҲ Set.Ico s t,
          вҖ–galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) mвҖ–
            вүӨ MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m := by
        intros П„ hП„
        have h_П„_nn : 0 вүӨ П„ := le_trans hs hП„.1
        have h_pt := galerkinRHS_norm_le_latticeNorm_mul_l2_sum (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„) m
        have h_l2 := hEnergy n П„ h_П„_nn
        calc вҖ–galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) mвҖ–
            вүӨ latticeNorm m * вҲ‘ m' : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–Оұ n П„ m'вҖ– ^ 2 := h_pt
          _ вүӨ latticeNorm m * MвӮӮ :=
              mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left h_l2 (latticeNorm_nonneg m)
          _ = MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m := by ring
      have h_deriv_local : вҲҖ П„ вҲҲ Set.Ico s t,
          HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
            (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n)
              (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
            (Set.Ici П„) П„ := fun П„ hП„ =>
        hDeriv n П„ (le_trans hs hП„.1) m hm
      have h_lip := galerkinExtend_mode_lipschitz_of_ODE_bound
        (sqgBox n) (Оұ n) m (MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m) hst
        h_deriv_local (hCont n m hm s t hs hst) h_bound
      calc вҖ–galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t) m - galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n s) mвҖ–
          вүӨ MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m * (t - s) := h_lip
        _ = MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m * (t - s) := rfl
    В· -- t вүӨ s: reverse.
      have h_abs : |t - s| = s - t := by
        rw [abs_of_nonpos (sub_nonpos.mpr hts), neg_sub]
      rw [h_abs]
      have h_bound : вҲҖ П„ вҲҲ Set.Ico t s,
          вҖ–galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) mвҖ–
            вүӨ MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m := by
        intros П„ hП„
        have h_П„_nn : 0 вүӨ П„ := le_trans ht hП„.1
        have h_pt := galerkinRHS_norm_le_latticeNorm_mul_l2_sum (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„) m
        have h_l2 := hEnergy n П„ h_П„_nn
        calc вҖ–galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) mвҖ–
            вүӨ latticeNorm m * вҲ‘ m' : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–Оұ n П„ m'вҖ– ^ 2 := h_pt
          _ вүӨ latticeNorm m * MвӮӮ :=
              mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left h_l2 (latticeNorm_nonneg m)
          _ = MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m := by ring
      have h_deriv_local : вҲҖ П„ вҲҲ Set.Ico t s,
          HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
            (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n)
              (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
            (Set.Ici П„) П„ := fun П„ hП„ =>
        hDeriv n П„ (le_trans ht hП„.1) m hm
      have h_lip := galerkinExtend_mode_lipschitz_of_ODE_bound
        (sqgBox n) (Оұ n) m (MвӮӮ * latticeNorm m) hts
        h_deriv_local (hCont n m hm t s ht hts) h_bound
      rw [norm_sub_rev]
      exact h_lip
  В· -- m вҲү sqgBox n: both galerkinExtend values are 0.
    rw [galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm,
        galerkinExtend_apply_of_not_mem _ _ hm, sub_zero, norm_zero]
    exact mul_nonneg
      (mul_nonneg hMвӮӮ_nn (latticeNorm_nonneg m))
      (abs_nonneg _)

/-! ### В§10.172.E `HasModeLipschitzFamily` from `LВІ` conservation (structured)

Wires В§10.172.D into `HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkinBounds`
(В§10.152), producing a full `HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ` structure from
the equality form of Galerkin `LВІ` conservation (В§10.97).  The
`LВІ`-bound form required by В§10.172.D follows from the equality form
via `sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq` (В§10.119 Parseval bound). -/

/-- **`HasModeLipschitzFamily` from `LВІ` conservation alone.**
Composes В§10.172.D with В§10.152's `HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkinBounds`
via the `sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq` Parseval bridge.  Produces a
per-mode Lipschitz family with `modeLipschitz m = (вҲ« вҖ–ОёвӮҖвҖ–ВІ) В· latticeNorm m`,
uniform in `n`.

This is the **Item 1 analytical closure**: combined with В§10.165's
`sqgGalerkin_hExtract_witness` and В§10.155.B's
`HasPerModeLimit.ofModeLipschitzFamily`, it discharges Item 1's
remaining `hH2` hypothesis structurally, using only classical
`LВІ`-conservation + the ODE hypotheses supplied by В§10.116. -/
noncomputable def HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkin_l2_conservation
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ОёвӮҖ : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hEnergy : вҲҖ n t, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      (вҲ‘ m : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–Оұ n t mвҖ– ^ 2)
        = вҲ‘ m : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–fourierRestrict n ОёвӮҖ mвҖ– ^ 2)
    (hDeriv : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ), 0 вүӨ П„ вҶ’ вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’
      HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
        (Set.Ici П„) П„)
    (hCont : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’ вҲҖ (s t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ t вҶ’
      ContinuousOn (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (Set.Icc s t)) :
    HasModeLipschitzFamily Оұ :=
  HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkinBounds ОёвӮҖ hEnergy
    (fun m => (вҲ« x, вҖ–ОёвӮҖ xвҖ– ^ 2) * latticeNorm m)
    (fun m => mul_nonneg
      (integral_nonneg (fun _ => sq_nonneg _))
      (latticeNorm_nonneg m))
    (fun n m s t hs ht =>
      sqgGalerkin_modeLipschitz_from_l2_conservation ОёвӮҖ
        (fun n' t' ht' => (hEnergy n' t' ht').le.trans
          (sum_sq_fourierRestrict_le_L2Sq n' ОёвӮҖ))
        hDeriv hCont n m s t hs ht)

/-! ### В§10.172.F Item 1 capstone вҖ” `HasPerModeLimit` from `LВІ` conservation

Composes В§10.172.E with В§10.165 (`sqgGalerkin_hExtract_witness`) and
В§10.155.B (`HasPerModeLimit.ofModeLipschitzFamily`) into a single
existence theorem: from Galerkin `LВІ` conservation + the ODE
hypotheses supplied by В§10.116, produce a `HasPerModeLimit Оұ` witness
**unconditionally** (no `hH2` hypothesis).

This is the **maximally-closed form** of Item 1 reachable from the
current infrastructure: the remaining step to a full `SqgSolution`
(the `HasFourierSynthesis` construction) is handled separately by
В§10.159 (`ofSummable`) or В§10.164 (`ofTight`), both of which reduce
the synthesis step to elementary tightness/summability hypotheses. -/

/-- **В§10.172.F Item 1 capstone: `HasPerModeLimit` from `LВІ` conservation.**
Unconditional production of the per-mode limit structure from the
Galerkin `LВІ` conservation hypothesis, closing Item 1's `hH2`-style
analytic gap. -/
noncomputable def HasPerModeLimit.ofSqgGalerkin_l2_conservation
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ОёвӮҖ : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hEnergy : вҲҖ n t, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      (вҲ‘ m : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–Оұ n t mвҖ– ^ 2)
        = вҲ‘ m : вҶҘ(sqgBox n), вҖ–fourierRestrict n ОёвӮҖ mвҖ– ^ 2)
    (hDeriv : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (П„ : в„қ), 0 вүӨ П„ вҶ’ вҲҖ (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’
      HasDerivWithinAt (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (galerkinRHS (sqgBox n) (galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n П„)) m)
        (Set.Ici П„) П„)
    (hCont : вҲҖ (n : в„•) (m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө), m вҲҲ sqgBox n вҶ’ вҲҖ (s t : в„қ), 0 вүӨ s вҶ’ s вүӨ t вҶ’
      ContinuousOn (fun Пғ => galerkinExtend (sqgBox n) (Оұ n Пғ) m)
        (Set.Icc s t)) :
    HasPerModeLimit Оұ :=
  let lip := HasModeLipschitzFamily.ofSqgGalerkin_l2_conservation
    ОёвӮҖ hEnergy hDeriv hCont
  HasPerModeLimit.ofModeLipschitzFamily lip (sqgGalerkin_hExtract_witness lip)

/-! ### В§10.173 `BKMCriterionHighFreq` off the finite-Fourier-support
class for arbitrary `s > 1` (lifts the `s вүӨ 2` restriction of В§10.168)

Parallel to В§10.168.A but uses the **generic-`s`** `BKMCriterionHighFreq`
in place of `BKMCriterionS2`.  В§10.167.A's LSC lemma is generic in
`s` already, so dropping the `s вүӨ 2` hypothesis is structural вҖ” no
new analytic content needed.

The call-site must supply uniform `бёўЛў` bounds at every `s > 1`
(not just `s вҲҲ (1, 2]`).  This is the **extension path** for Item 5
of `OPEN.md`: with high-`s` uniform Galerkin bounds supplied (either
unconditionally via a smooth initial data argument + KatoвҖ“Ponce, or
axiomatically for a specific problem), conditional Theorem 3 extends
to every `s вүҘ 0`. -/

/-- **В§10.173.A  `BKMCriterionHighFreq` from an `LВІ`-limit sequence
with uniform `бёўЛў` control at every `s > 1`.**  Drops the `s вүӨ 2`
restriction of В§10.168.A. -/
theorem BKMCriterionHighFreq.of_L2_limit_uniform_Hs_all_s
    (Оё : в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (fвӮҷ : в„• вҶ’ в„қ вҶ’ Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2))))
    (hConv : вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’
      Filter.Tendsto (fun n => вҲ« x, вҖ–fвӮҷ n t x - Оё t xвҖ– ^ 2)
        Filter.atTop (nhds 0))
    (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hSumm_fn : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’
      Summable (fun m : Fin 2 вҶ’ в„Ө =>
        (fracDerivSymbol s m) ^ 2 * вҖ–mFourierCoeff (fвӮҷ n t) mвҖ– ^ 2))
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (fвӮҷ n t) вүӨ Ms s) :
    BKMCriterionHighFreq Оё where
  hsPropagationHighFreq := fun _ s hs1 =>
    вҹЁMs s, fun t ht =>
      (hsSeminormSq_le_of_L2_limit_uniform_bound (s := s) (M := Ms s)
        (hConv t ht)
        (fun n => hSumm_fn n t ht s hs1)
        (fun n => hBound n t ht s hs1)).2вҹ©

/-- **В§10.173.B  `BKMCriterionHighFreq` for the AubinвҖ“Lions limit.**
Specialises В§10.173.A to `HasAubinLionsExtraction`.  Summability of
the weighted family comes for free from the finite Fourier support
of each Galerkin state via `hsSeminormSq_summable_galerkinToLp`. -/
theorem BKMCriterionHighFreq.of_aubinLions_uniform_Hs_all_s
    {Оё : Lp в„Ӯ 2 (volume : Measure (UnitAddTorus (Fin 2)))}
    {Оұ : вҲҖ n : в„•, в„қ вҶ’ (вҶҘ(sqgBox n) вҶ’ в„Ӯ)}
    (ext : HasAubinLionsExtraction Оё Оұ)
    (Ms : в„қ вҶ’ в„қ)
    (hBound : вҲҖ n : в„•, вҲҖ t : в„қ, 0 вүӨ t вҶ’ вҲҖ s : в„қ, 1 < s вҶ’
      hsSeminormSq s (galerkinToLp (sqgBox n) (Оұ n t)) вүӨ Ms s) :
    BKMCriterionHighFreq ext.Оё_lim := by
  refine BKMCriterionHighFreq.of_L2_limit_uniform_Hs_all_s
    (Оё := ext.Оё_lim)
    (fвӮҷ := fun k t => galerkinToLp (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t))
    ?_ Ms ?_ ?_
  В· intro t ht
    exact ext.tendsto_L2 t ht
  В· intro k t _ s _
    exact hsSeminormSq_summable_galerkinToLp s
      (sqgBox (ext.nsub k)) (Оұ (ext.nsub k) t)
  В· intro k t ht s hs1
    exact hBound (ext.nsub k) t ht s hs1

/-! ### В§10.174 Full-range Theorem 3 on the AubinвҖ“Lions limit

